title: angel salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups hot water.
Add cream cheese. Dissolve and cool.
Add undrained pineapple, fruit cocktail and marshmallows.
Mix and let congeal.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator until set.

title: hot dog gravy
directions: Heat grease and brown hot dogs.
Then, add flour and mix in until it bubbles.
Add enough milk to make gravy.
Add salt and pepper and cook until it is the right thickness.
Serve on toasted bread.

title: the impossible cream
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender or food processor.
Blend for 30 seconds. Grease oven dish and pour in mixed ingredients. Bake at 350° to 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Combine with soup, broth and green chilies.
Add pieces of boned chicken and beat well.
In a a large baking dish, place a layer of chicken sauce, then a layer of cheese and tortillas.
Repeat until casserole is filled.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: starfinder cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl cream together butter, brown sugar and honey.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, dry milk, wheat germ, salt and baking soda.
Add to batter, stirring well.
Fold in toasted oats cereal. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheet. Flatten with fork.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini crabmeat quiche
directions: Form rolls into crust.
Saute zucchini and mushrooms in butter.
Add crabmeat, drained and washed.
Beat eggs adding garlic, salt, dill weed and pepper.
Pour over zucchini mixture in pie shell.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Garnish with parsley.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes; drain well. Combine soup, eggs, mayonnaise and diced cheese; mix well.
Add drained broccoli.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs or dressing mix over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil 1 whole chicken.
Take off bone.
Add 1 to 2 cans of chicken soup to juice.
Take crescent rolls and slice each roll in half.
Boil in broth for 1 to 2 minutes on each side.
Take them up as you cook them and set aside.

title: quick casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in pan.
Put in a 350° oven for 20 to 40 minutes.

title: rice-a-roni meatballs
directions: Cook shells in hot water with salt and oil for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and cool before stuffing.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together and freeze.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken jalapeno
directions: Stew chicken; cook and chop.
Line bottom of casserole with Doritos.
Mix soups and broth.
Stir chopped chicken in this mixture and add a little salt and pepper.
Pour over Doritos. Heat well in 350° oven.
When it becomes bubbly, sprinkle cheese over the top and heat until cheese is melted.

title: red and white bean salad
directions: Chop and mix well; let set before serving.

title: pudding chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda and baking powder, set aside. Combine butter, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy, beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture then stir in chips and nuts.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Drop from teaspoons onto greased baking sheets, 2 in. apart.
Bake at 375° for 8-10 minutes.
Don't overcook.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in 2 tablespoons butter or margarine for 10 minutes.
Mix together the zucchini, onion, bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper to taste and the eggs.
Melt butter or margarine in large frypan.
Pour in zucchini and egg mixture and cook without stirring until bottom is set.
Put frypan under broiler to cook the top.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat at number 2 speed about 5 minutes on electric mixer. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Combine crushed cookies and melted margarine.
Pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve 1 cup for top.
Mix instant pudding, milk, softened cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Pour mixture over crust.
Sprinkle reserved cookie mixture over top. Refrigerate to set.

title: double chocolate bars
directions: Combine cake mix, butter, and 1 egg.
Beat at low speed until smooth.
Reserve 2/3 cup of this mixture and set aside.
Press remaining cake mixture into a greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pig out cake
directions: Beat yellow cake mix, mandarin oranges and juice, oil and eggs.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Combine Cool Whip, vanilla pudding and crushed pineapple with juice and put on top of cake.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat until well blended.
Add melted margarine and beat well again.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in carrots and nuts.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Heat butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion; cook 8 minutes or until tender.
Stir in flour until blended; cook, stirring, 1 minute.
Add water, potatoes and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Lower heat; simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are to your desired doneness.
Add clam meat; cook 3 minutes.
Add cream (milk); cook just until heated through.
Ladle into bowls and garnish with parsley.
Serve with oyster crackers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: casserole surprise
directions: Put 3/4 pound ground beef in bottom of cold electric frypan. Layer vegetables over meat and add remaining 1/4 pound ground beef on top of vegetables.
Pour soup over meat and vegetables, spreading to edges of frypan.
Top with cheese and cook over medium heat (300°) for 30 to 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender and mixture is bubbly.

title: byerly's chocolate mousse
directions: Melt chocolate chips; stir in coffee and liqueur.
Let cool to room temperature; stir in egg yolks.
Whip 1/2 cup cream until thickened; gradually whip in 2 tablespoons sugar until stiff peaks form.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Gently fold egg whites into whipped cream.
Stir about 1/3 whipped mixture into chocolate.
Fold in remaining whipped mixture.
Pour into 8 individual dessert cups or dishes.
Refrigerate until set, about 2 hours.

title: eggplant fries
directions: Cut eggplant into strips.
Season flour with salt and pepper. Dip strips in buttermilk, then dredge in flour.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: chalupa dip
directions: Mix together refried beans and bean dip.
Spread on 9 x 12-inch glass serving or baking dish.
Then mix together sour cream, mayonnaise and picante sauce and spread over beans.
Next, mix avocados, salt, pepper and lemon juice and spread over sour cream layer.
Then sprinkle grated cheese over avocados.
Layer tomatoes, lettuce and onions over grated cheese.
If desired, spread more cheese over lettuce and tomato layer.
Top with sliced olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: glaeshia's bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and mix wet ingredients together. Mix wet and dry together.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Set at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: tomato rice soup
directions: Put 2 cups of water in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add rice, onion, green pepper, celery and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add bacon bits and tomatoes; stir well.
Remove from heat and let set for 10 minutes to insure rice is done.
Add 1 tablespoon butter, if desired.

title: good for you juice
directions: Mix and refrigerate.
Drink 1/2 to 1 cup daily.

title: heavenly lemon pie
directions: Beat 4 egg whites until frothy; add 1 cup sugar, sifted with cream of tartar.
Whip until it holds a stiff, glossy peak. Spread the mixture in a well-greased 9-inch pie pan (spread it to the edges with a slight recession in the center) and bake one hour at 275°.
Let cool.
Mix lemon juice, rind, 4 egg yolks (beaten) and 1/2 cup sugar.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until real thick (8 to 10 minutes).
Cool.
Then fold in 1/2 pint whipped cream or 1 package beaten Dream Whip.
Put into baked shell, making sure all pockets are filled.
Whip up remaining cream or Dream Whip and put on top.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: nacho cheese sauce
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain and crumble into small pieces.
Add cheese and peppers and melt in microwave or crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a saucepan.
Add onion and cook until clear.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Add potatoes.
Remove from heat when soup bubbles again.
Add pepper to taste.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese.
Add peanut butter and powdered sugar; beat on low just until blended.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: sun gold coconut cake
directions: Beat eggs and shortening together until smooth and creamy. Beat egg yolks until foamy.
Stir into mixture; beat until very light.
Add dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Carefully fold into batter.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool and ice with your favorite white icing.
Sprinkle coconut over cake.

title: quail baked in wine
directions: Melt fat, add onions, cloves, peppercorns, garlic and bay leaf; cook for several minutes.
Add quail and brown on all sides.
Add wine, salt, pepper, cayenne and chives and simmer until tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove quail to hot serving dish.
Strain sauce, add cream and heat to boiling point.
Pour over quail.
Allow 1 quail for each serving.

title: sausage balls
directions: Roll into small balls and bake about 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chow mein cookies(these cookies require no baking)
directions: Cook syrup and sugar to boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and noodles.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Makes 24.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes about 1/2-inch thick. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper.
Dust slices with flour on all sides.
Pour oil into a large frying pan to depth of about 1/4-inch.
Place over medium heat. While oil heats, dip tomato slices into egg to coat on all sides. Fry tomatoes, about half at a time, turning once, until golden brown on all sides.
Serve hot.

title: orange pineapple congealed salad
directions: In large sauce pan, combine jello and pineapple, with juice. Heat to a low boil.
Stir in Cool Whip, stirring constantly.
When Cool Whip is dissolved, remove from heat, add pecans.
Pour into 13 x 9 glass casserole or large jello mold.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: pudding a cloud
directions: Spoon 1/3 cup of Cool Whip into each of 6 dessert glasses. Using back of spoon, make depression in center and spread topping up sides of each glass.
Prepare pudding mix with milk as directed on package.
Spoon pudding mixture into glasses.
Chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef; add chopped onion and other seasonings. Add catsup to cover and a little more.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook pasta, drain. Cut up crab meat, onion, celery and carrots. Add to pasta. Combine miracle whip and Italian dressing. Pour over pasta and mix.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Use electric mixer to beat cheese and Miracle Whip together.
Add other ingredients and stir in sour cream.
One-half of this recipe is enough for a small crowd.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Cream pumpkin, eggs and sugar. Add salt and milk. Put in Pammed cake pan. Top with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: purdue dressing(makes 1 pint)
directions: Beat everything together with wire whisk.
Refrigerate.

title: taco pie(low calorie)
directions: Press rolls into pie plate or iron skillet.
Brown turkey.
Add bouillon, onion and bell pepper.
Add tomato paste, water and taco seasoning.
Mix well; put 1/2 turkey mixture in crust.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese, add remaining turkey.
Top with rest of cheese. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: * Four tablespoons Equal may be substituted for sugar.

title: tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in large pan.
Cook slow over low-medium heat until cooked and thick, about 2 hours.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Saute garlic in oil 5 minutes.
Discard garlic.
Brown cutlets in oil.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over meat. Add onion and wine.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, turning meat several times.
Add more liquid (wine or tomato juice) if needed. Add mushrooms; cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes more.
Serve with sauce.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bloody mary soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until limp and golden.
Add tomato puree and sugar.
Cook 1 minute.
Add tomato juice and simmer 8 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and strain.
Return strained mixture to heat and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Refrigerate 4 hours or more.
Serve in bouillon cups and flame a tablespoon of vodka on top.
The soup also can be served in well chilled, salt-rimmed low glasses.

title: chicken and rice soup with celery tops
directions: Simmer chicken in water for 1 hour.
Take chicken out and set aside.
Strain broth and place back in pot.
Into broth, add vegetables and bouillon cubes.
Chop chicken and return to pot. Simmer for 30 minutes.
May add more water.

title: lady baltimore cake
directions: Sift
flour,
baking
powder
and
salt 3 times.
Cream butter until
light and fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Add 1 1/2 cups sugar gradually and cream until like whipped cream.
Add flour and
milk alternately
in
small amounts.
Begin and end with flour.
Mix after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding 1/2 cup sugar.
Beat until glossy.
Fold egg whites into batter and mix thoroughly.	Turn into 3 (8-inch or 9-inch)	layer pans.
Bake
at 350° to 375° for about 25 minutes.	Cool in the pans.
Turn out and frost.

title: clams la ray
directions: Scrub and shuck the clams.
Save the shells* and reserve the liquid. Chop the clams.

title: veal scaloppine
directions: Cut veal into pieces 1 to 3-inches square.
Shake in bag with flour, salt and pepper; set aside when pieces are well floured.
In skillet, add olive oil and garlic until lightly brown.
Add veal to garlic and oil.
Brown on both sides.
While veal is browning, combine tomatoes, wine, salt, parsley, oregano, pepper, green pepper and mushrooms.
Add this mixture to browned veal.
Cover skillet.
Simmer for 25 minutes or until veal is tender.
If mixture becomes too thick, add small amount water.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream the butter and cheese.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Roll thin, about 1/8-inch.
Bake at 350°.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Put in two 9-inch baked pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm.

title: potato refrigerator rolls
directions: Mash potatoes; add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs together in mixing bowl.
Dissolve yeast in water.
Add dissolved yeast to the milk, then add to potato mixture.
Add sifted flour to make a stiff dough.
Toss on floured board and knead well.
Put in large greased mixing bowl and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Knead lightly.
Shape into rolls or put into refrigerator until ready to use.
Let rolls rise until doubled in bulk.
Place in 425° oven until golden brown.

title: ice cream pie
directions: Bake and cook 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Toast in frypan the coconut, pecans and 1/2 stick butter.

title: yum yum dessert
directions: Melt oleo and crush cookies; mix together.
Hold out 1/3 cup. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add to mixture ice cream.
Spread on crumbs.
Spread whipped topping on top. Sprinkle 1/3 cup of crumbs on top.

title: dinner rolls
directions: No kneading. Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: orange blossoms
directions: Mix cake mix as directed for cupcakes.
Bake in greased and floured miniature muffin pans.
Remove pans immediately and dip into glaze.
Remove from glaze and drain on wax paper.
May be frozen.

title: strawberry-pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, 3 tablespoons
sugar and melted margarine together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix
cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and topping together.
Spread on
top
of
cooled
pretzel
layer. Dissolve Jell-O
in
boiling
water;
add
strawberries,
let partially set.
When Jell-O
mixture is partially firm, spread on top of cheese layer and chill thoroughly.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a mixing bowl, cream margarine and sugar until smooth, then beat in egg and vanilla.
Separately in a larger bowl, mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt, then stir in oats and raisins.
Add butter-sugar mixture and stir to make a sticky dough.
Drop by the rounded tablespoon on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before trying to remove cookies from baking sheet.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: calico beans
directions: Call Dominos at 325-7777.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on a large dinner type plate. Spread a layer of cocktail sauce over the cream cheese.
Then sprinkle the shrimp over the cocktail sauce.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: sausage rice casserole(yields 6 servings)
directions: Brown, drain and rinse sausage.
Saute celery and onion in small amount of butter.
Combine boiling water, chicken noodle soup and 1/2 cup of rice and boil for 7 minutes.
Combine soup mixture with sausage, onion and celery.
Bake in casserole for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Mix together Jell-O, water and marshmallows.
Add mayonnaise, cottage cheese and pineapple.
Chill until set.
Can be frozen. Can add grated carrots or chopped nuts for topping.

title: peanut butter penuche
directions: Cook sugar, cream and butter into soft ball (238°).
When cool, add vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until firm and creamy. Spread out and cut into squares after kneading.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown beef with onions.
Drain.
In a large baking dish, cream together refried beans, sour cream and salsa.
Add browned, drained beef and cheese; stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese melts completely through.
Stir occasionally.
Serve hot with white tortilla chips.

title: lipton miniature meat turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, combine mushroom mix with meat, bean sprouts, water chestnuts and onion.
Brown well. Separate crescent dough according to package directions, then cut each triangle in half.
Place a teaspoonful of meat mixture in center of each small triangle.
Fold over and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 32 turnovers.

title: pizza paparella
directions: In large bowl mix sugar, yeast and water.
Let yeast bubble (this makes sure your yeast will work); add flour 1 cup at a time, stirring in between, add salt between 2nd and 3rd cups.
Dough should be soft but not wet.

title: sausage balls
directions: Allow cheese and sausage to come to room temperature.
Mix together all ingredients and knead until well blended.
Roll into 1-2 inch size balls.
Bake at 400 degrees 15-20 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Line a small bowl with foil.
Use fingers to blend first 6 ingredients.
Pour mixture in bowl.
Chill.
Combine last 4 ingredients and pour over mold after unmolding, just before serving.

title: holiday cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pretty baking dish and cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve immediately with crackers.

title: crock-pot gingery bean bake
directions: In 3 1/2, 4, 5 or 6-quart crockery cooker, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Cover.
Cook over low heat setting for 5 to 6 hours or on high heat setting for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; save broth.
Boil spaghetti, debone and chop chicken into bite size.
Shred cheeses.
Saute onions, bell pepper and garlic in margarine.
Add 3 cans of soup and 1/2 of cheese mixture to coat vegetables and mix.
Stir in chicken and spaghetti.
Pour into baking dish and bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake until melted.

title: oil free muffins
directions: Mix milk, egg whites and syrup; blend with dry ingredients. Bake in muffin tins for 13 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Saute onions and celery in oil until crisp.
Add the next 5 ingredients; simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in cornstarch with water, a little at a time.
Cook until thickened.

title: apricot delight
directions: In a large bowl, combine Jell-O and pineapple.
Heat in microwave until Jell-O dissolves when stirred.
Add sugar, baby food and softened cream cheese.
Cream together until melted. Refrigerate until egg white consistency.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate until served.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Bring to boil.
Drop in a few peaches at a time and cook until tender.
Continue this process until syrup is used up.
Will do about 24 peaches.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt stick of butter in baking dish.
Meanwhile, mix remaining ingredients and pour over butter.
Add pie filling on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Make well in center of dry ingredients and pour liquids into it.
Mix only long enough to mix dry ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 cupcake size muffins or 24 mini muffins (watch time after 10 minutes).

title: wet bottom shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and Crisco like pie dough for crumbs. Take out 2 cups of crumbs for top of pies.
To the remainder of crumbs in the bowl, add eggs, King syrup and hot water.
Mix well. Dissolve soda in an extra 1/2 cup of hot water and add to other liquid mixture.

title: lemon freeze
directions: Butter 8-inch square baking pan.
Combine butter, brown sugar and nutmeg.
Add nuts and Chex crumbs.
Mix.
Reserve 1/2 cup for topping.
Press remainder evenly into bottom of pan.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: pistachio jello salad
directions: Mix
dry
pudding
mix with pineapple, marshmallows and lemon juice.
Then add Cool Whip and mix well again.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and celery until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: mackerel loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients together except butter and ketchup in a bowl and knead together to form a loaf.
Then place it in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Put ketchup and drops of butter on top and put in oven preheated to 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a well-greased casserole. Dot the top with butter.
Bake at 350° for 80 minutes, 400° last 10 minutes.

title: carrot puffs
directions: Cook carrots, cover, in a small portion of boiling salted water 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Mash carrots, and let cool.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Add onion, salt, bell pepper and garlic. Cook a minute.
Then add soups.
Cook until hot and mixed well. Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Mix in cooked egg noodles or pour meat over cooked egg noodles.

title: cinnamon diamonds
directions: Heat
oven
Line a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan
with
foil.
Mix flour and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
In large bowl,
beat
butter and brown sugar with electric mixer until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk.
Stir in flour mixture until blended. Then
add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Spread in pan.
For topping, beat egg whites with a fork until frothy, brush over dough.
Mix granulated
sugar,
the
remaining
teaspoon cinnamon
and 1/2
cup nuts.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes
until lightly
brown.
Cool slightly in pan on rack. Lift
foil by ends onto a cutting board, while still warm, cut baked dough into 2-inch diamonds.
Makes 36.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn bread mix.
Add corn bread mix last.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown on top.
It will be soft inside.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy and mix all other ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400 degree oven for 15 minutes and reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for 30 to 35 minutes more.

title: beef short ribs with onions and prunes
directions: In Dutch oven or deep iron skillet, heat oil and brown short ribs.
Remove and drain.
Pour off excess oil from skillet.
Place short ribs back in container.
Add water to cover and seasonings; cover.
Cook until fork-tender.
Add onions and prunes. Cook until prunes are soft.
You may need to add water during cooking. Thicken, if needed, with cornstarch or flour paste.
Serve over rice.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine filling ingredients, mixing well. Pour into pie crust and bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool pies down and garnish with whipped topping and nuts.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put flour and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Bring next 4 ingredients to a boil, then add to flour and sugar.
Add soda and buttermilk mixture with eggs and vanilla.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan for 20 minutes at 400°.
Spread on icing while still warm.

title: chicken francois
directions: Place boned skinned chicken breasts in oblong pan . Cover each with a slice of Swiss cheese. Mix cream of mushroom soup with cooking sherry and milk. Can use evaporated milk (low-fat). Pour on top of casserole. Cover with a layer of Pepperidge Farm corn bread stuffing mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour to
1 hour 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: summer squash with taste
directions: Place bacon and onion in medium saucepan over medium heat and cook until onion is transparent, being careful not to scorch them. Add the squash and simmer until the squash is tender.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: chicken and dressing(quick, easy and good)
directions: Place deboned chicken in casserole.
Saute onion and celery in vegetable-sprayed skillet until transparent.
Add dressing mix and enough broth from chicken to moisture is of desired consistency. Pour undiluted chicken soup over meat and dressing mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup dressing mix.
Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly dirt flower
directions: Mix everything, except the oreos.
Pour into a "Flower Pot." Top with crushed oreos (take the white filling out of the oreo). Garnish with gummy worms and artificial flower.
Kids really like this.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Mix
together jello, water, pineapple and strawberries. Pour 1/2 of this
mixture into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
(Set the remainder
aside
at
room	temperature.)
Refrigerate the first half of
the
mixture
until set.
Spread sour cream on, then pour the
remainder
of	the mixture over the sour cream. Refrigerate until set.

title: microwave potato soup
directions: Place onion, margarine, potatoes and salt in a 2 1/2-quart glass casserole.
Cover; microwave on High for 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Blend flour and cream together; pour over potatoes and microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes, or until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Top with crumbled bacon and serve.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Cut, wash and drain vegetables.
Mix Ranch dressing with mayonnaise and sour cream.	Add onions and cheese.	Mix and pour over vegetables.
Stir and refrigerate before serving.

title: seashell salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate and serve cold on lettuce or not, as you wish.

title: one pan dinner
directions: Mix ingredients and cook until tender.
Serve with applesauce or fruit of choice.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and spread evenly on tortillas approximately 1/8 inch thick.
Roll tortillas and refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Remove from refrigerator and cut into 1-inch pieces. Place toothpick in each piece and dip in salsa.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine cookie mix, 1 egg white, almond extract and 1/2 of coconut.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip into remaining egg white.
Roll into remaining coconut.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press candied cherry half into center of each cookie. Bake at 375° for 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to cooling rack.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Put flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt, sifted together in a bowl.
Add oil and hot water and mix well (use electric beater). Beat in eggs.
Add baking powder sifted on top and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 325° for about 50 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add the remaining ingredients, and simmer on low heat until hot.

title: broccoli parmesan(low-fat)
directions: Cut broccoli into thin spears.
Arrange on a large plate in a circular pattern, with the florets in the center and the stems at the rim.
Sprinkle with the water and thyme.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Rotate the dish a half turn.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes, or until the stems are easily pierced with a sharp knife.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Can be prepared ahead of time, except add Fritos and cheese just before serving.

title: kaiserschmarrn(german pancake)
directions: Prepare batter with flour, salt, milk and egg yolks.
Add melted butter, raisins and rum extract.
Mix well.
Gradually fold the beaten egg whites into batter.
In large pan, melt some butter and pour a layer of batter (1/2-inch thick) and fry until brown. Turn and brown other side.
When both sides have been browned, using forks, tear pancake into 1-inch squares.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Serve hot.

title: yellow squash casserole(from white house kitchen)
directions: Note:
Try grating 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg and 1/4 cup sugar to make a pie or quiche.

title: sesame spinach
directions: Mix together the soy sauce, sesame oil and sugar.
Heat the oil in a skillet or wok.
Add garlic, ginger and scallions.
Saute over medium heat for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add spinach and stir-fry until cooked, but still crispy (2 to 3 minutes).
Add soy mixture and heat through.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: cherry delight
directions: Place cherry filling in the bottom of a 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over cherries.
Pour the butter over that, then sprinkle with the nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: peanut butter delights
directions: Melt butter in pot over medium heat.
Add cocoa, salt, evaporated milk and sugar.
Stir until it boils; boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and quick oats; stir.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool 30 minutes.
Cut.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well eggs, white sugar, oil and water.
In separate bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Blend second mixture into first.
Pour into one large greased loaf pan or into 3 small loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: crustless apple pie
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 40 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Mix flour and cinnamon with sliced apples in a bowl.
Put 38 caramels in a 2-cup measuring dish with 3 tablespoons water.
Melt in microwave, stirring every 30 seconds until melted.
Mix melted caramel with apple mixture and put in pie crust.

title: artichoke cream soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the onion, celery and green bell pepper in the butter until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add the flour and cook, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Slowly add the chicken broth and lemon juice, stirring until blended.
Add the bay leaves, thyme and chopped artichoke hearts.
Cover and simmer until thickened, about 20 minutes.

title: home-cured ham baked in milk
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease a large flat casserole.
Mix mustard and sugar together. Spread over ham.
Place meat in the casserole and add enough milk to cover.
Bake until milk has reduced in volume and ham has browned lightly, 45 minutes to 1 hour. Remove from oven and serve immediately.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Gradually add broth and milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add cauliflower and cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.

title: rocky road cookies
directions: Mix margarine, milk, cocoa and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes.
Slice across the top crosswise.
Be sure not to cut all the way through.
Slice onions very thin.
Take a slice of onion and put one in each slit of the potato.
Melt butter and dribble over the top.
Wrap up in foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve as a meal or with your favorite meal.

title: cheesy chicken roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat can of Campbell's soup with 1/2 to 1 can water.
Add Veg-All (optional) to this (drained).

title: no peek steak
directions: Brown meat and fresh mushrooms.
Combine rest of ingredients. Place in slow cooker and cook on high, 5 to 6 hours or on low, 6 to 8 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: swiss tomato pie *
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange croutons in 9-inch pie plate. Top croutons with tomato slices and shredded cheese.
In a small bowl, beat remaining ingredients with a wire whisk.
Pour over cheese.
Bake until
puffy and golden brown, approximately 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: kahlua
directions: Add in order; mix well.
Store in bottle.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients with hands.
Shape loosely into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 100 cocktail size balls.

title: old timey molasses cake
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and molasses; blend thoroughly.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon and buttermilk.
Add at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and oil; add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Add carrots, pecans and pineapple. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: beefed up biscuits casserole
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and mangos.
Drain excess grease.
Stir in tomato sauce and chili powder; simmer.
Place 5 biscuits (spread out) on bottom of ungreased pan.
Combine 1/2 cup grated cheese and egg.
Mix well.
Remove meat mixture from heat and stir in cheese and egg mixture.
Spoon over biscuits.
Spread out remaining biscuits over meat and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 3 story apple pie
directions: Cook apples in small amount of water until tender; drain and add sugar.
Place in bottom of baked pie shell.

title: meringue shells and parfait filling
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 2/3 of the sugar until they hold their shape.
Fold in rest.
Shape into cup on heavy brown paper.
Bake 1 hour at 275° until dry, but not brown.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Drain marinade from one jar of artichokes into frying pan. Drain other jar and discard liquid.
Chop artichokes and set aside.
Add onion and garlic to pan and saute for 5 minutes.
In bowl, beat eggs; add crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and hot pepper. Stir in cheese, parsley, artichokes, onion and garlic.
Mix well. Turn into greased 11 x 7-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Cool; cut into 1-inch squares.
Serve warm or cold.

title: easy hamburger casserole
directions: Put lightly browned hamburger in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Layer the potatoes on top of the meat, then add onions, chopped green pepper and carrots.
Put tomatoes and seasonings next.
Last, top with
shredded cheese.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serves 6.

title: bagel dip
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, sour cream, diced onion, and dill weed. Mix well.
Fold in the chopped beef.
Chill.

title: holiday scallop
directions: Saute mushrooms and onions separately in butter.
Next, combine cottage cheese and sour cream.
Then layer ingredients in 2 good-sized casserole dishes in this order:
potatoes, onions, mushrooms and cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle each layer lightly with seasonings and grated cheese.
Keep layering until all ingredients are used up, ending with grated cheese on top.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°; remove cover for last 15 minutes of baking.
If you don't want to bake both casseroles at once, deliver one to a friend.
It will keep nicely in the refrigerator for a day or two before baking.
Serves 12.

title: cinnamon sugar and sugar glaze(part ii)
directions: Mix in plastic bag sugar and cinnamon.
Dip doughnuts in melted butter, then shake in sugar mixture; or for 10x sugar, shake in paper bag.

title: cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs. Add ingredients. Place on cookie sheet and bake until brown. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: 7 layer casserole
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish with tight lid, place rice or potatoes in layer and corn in layer; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour 1 can tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water over top. Place onion and green pepper in layer.
Pat out ground beef like a pie crust to fit on top of casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour on second can of tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water. Cover with strips of bacon cut in half.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake about 30 minutes longer, until bacon is crisp.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large pot combine onions, meat, vegetables, bay leaf and tomatoes.
Cook two hours on medium heat.
Add potatoes and salt. Cook until potatoes are soft.
Makes about one gallon.

title: no crust fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add eggs, sugar, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in greased pie pan for about 30 minutes at 325°. Do not preheat oven!
Start with cold oven.
This pie has no need for a pie crust; it forms its own.

title: lemon pie
directions: Thaw lemonade.
Mix 1/2 stick butter with enough graham cracker crumbs to cover the bottom and sides of a greased pie pan. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour into pie pan.
Top with a small amount of dry graham cracker crumbs.
Refrigerate until set.

title: nanaimo bars
directions: Blend 1/2 cup butter, 1/4 cup sugar, 5 teaspoons unsweetened cocoa and 1 beaten egg in double boiler until smooth. Mix 2 cups graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup chopped walnuts and 1 cup grated coconut with previous ingredients and press into buttered square pan.
Cool in refrigerator about 15 minutes.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in order given. Mix rest of ingredients. Sprinkle bacon bits on top. Make 24 hours ahead.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in a large pot, covering chicken with water. Boil until chicken is falling apart.
Remove when done to cool. Add rice to broth; cook until almost done.
(While rice is cooking, tear chicken off bone and into bite size pieces.)
When rice is almost done and water is almost absorbed, add cream of mushroom soup and chicken pieces.
Stir and simmer until rice is completely done.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls. Place on slightly greased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: praline sweet potatoes
directions: About an hour before serving:
Peel sweet potatoes.
Cut each potato crosswise into thirds.
In an 8-quart saucepot, cover potatoes to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, or until tender.
Drain; return to pot.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	except	bacon; pour into baking dish. Top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: perfect chicken
directions: In a regular size (10 x 16-inch) Reynolds oven cooking bag, shake flour into bag.
Add rice, butter, vegetables, broth and water; squeeze gently to blend.
Tie legs of chicken with string. Brush chicken with oil and sprinkle with seasonings.
Place chicken on top of rice and vegetables.
Close bag with nylon tie. Cut six 1/2-inch slits on top of bag.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until thigh moves easily.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes; open bag carefully.

title: banana bread
directions: Add bananas, sugar, eggs, margarine, soda dissolved in water and baking powder to flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Fry hamburger; add onion.
Add salt and pepper, pizza sauce and mushroom soup.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Serve on buns; top with cheese.
Broil until cheese melts (a few minutes).

title: bran wheat germ muffins
directions: Raisins and nuts can be added.

title: cheaters banana cake
directions: Thaw frozen bananas on plate.
Clabber milk with vinegar-set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Add baking soda to dry cake mix, add eggs, oil and clabbered milk to cake mix, blend.
Peel and mash bananas, add to cake, blend.
Add nuts if desired and blend.
Bake for 35-40 minutes.
Cool, add favorite topping or frosting.

title: susan's percolator brew
directions: Percolate ingredients and included basket ingredients until process stops, then enjoy this warm-up sipper.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil in a large kettle.
Add onions, garlic powder and celery salt.
Add cut up broccoli and cook until fork-tender.
Then add noodles and cook until done.
Add Velveeta cheese and stir until melted.
Add milk and gently heat to serving temperature.
This soup freezes well and reheats in the microwave very well.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and take meat off bones.
Saute the celery, green pepper and onion.
Add mushroom and tomato soups and chicken broth.
Add chicken.
Add chili powder and garlic.
Add spaghetti and cheeses.
Put in dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pork chops and dressing
directions: Flour chops and brown in melted butter or oleo.
Remove chops and put in a flat baking dish. Cook onion in the butter until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heap dressing onto the chops. Add 1/4 cup water and bake, covered, for 45 minutes or longer at 300°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo and shortening; add sugars, eggs and vanilla. Sift and add flour, baking powder and baking soda. Add oatmeal, chocolate chips, pecans, rice crispies and coconut. Use 1/4 c. measuring cup per cookie or ice cream scoop. Place on ungreased cookie sheet (6 cookies to a cookie sheet). Bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees. Let cool 5 minutes before removing from cookie sheet. Make 30 - 40 cookies.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Slice cucumbers and toss in a bowl with salt and pepper.
In a separate bowl combine cream cheese, sour cream and Italian dressing mix.
Spread cheese mixture on bread and top with cucumber slices.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: yum-yum cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in mixing bowl; blend well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 50 cookies.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oleo and oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir until oleo melts; add sugars and eggs.
Mix well. Continue mixing as sifted flour, soda and salt are added.
Stir in the cocoa and 1/2 of the package of chocolate chips.
Pour in greased pan.
Sprinkle nuts and remaining chocolate chips on top. Bake about 40 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: strawberry ice cream cake
directions: Tear pound cake into pieces. Layer all the ingredients in a dish of your choice. Top with whip cream. Freeze for a few hours. Serve.

title: salmon ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Stir in drained salmon, chopped onion and lemon juice.
Refrigerate.
When firm, roll in nuts and parsley.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: chocolate chip sandwiches
directions: Bake cookies as directed on package. When done, take out of oven and let cool for about 10 minutes. Put about 1 spoonful of Cool Whip between cookies to make a sandwich. Then pop into the freezer for about 30 minutes. Makes about a dozen sandwiches.

title: bran refrigerator rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine 3 cups of the flour and the yeast. Heat the water, shortening, sugar and 2 teaspoons salt just until warm, stirring constantly, until shortening almost melts.
Add to dry mixture eggs.
Beat at low speed on electric mixer for 1/2 minute.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in bran and remaining flour.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.

title: jello angel food cake
directions: Break cake in pieces in container that you are making Jell-O (I use a Bundt pan). Fix Jell-O in a bowl as directed on box. Pour over pieces of cake. Put in refrigerator until Jell-O is ready to eat (4 hours or longer).

title: chocolate layer cake
directions: Bake cake and split layers.
Mix the milk and flour and heat. Makes a thick paste; set aside. Cover with wax paper.
Whip together the sugar, mayonnaise, Crisco and vanilla.
Mix with paste and put between layers and ice with chocolate icing.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked
pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: zucchini surprise
directions: Brown sausage; set aside.
Saute onion and pepper in the sausage fat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 5 minutes. Pour into 2-quart baking dish, sprinkle with sausage.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
When done, sprinkle with the grated cheese.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown hamburger in iron skillet; drain.
Add onion, tomato sauce, salt, chili powder and corn; heat to boil.
Top with corn bread mix, prepared according to directions on box.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until corn bread is done.

title: scalloped green beans
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and blend well.
Add milk slowly and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add liquid from beans, mustard and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add salt and pepper.
Put alternate layers of beans and sauce into a well-greased uncovered casserole; top with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, until fluffy.
Add flour, one cup at a time, stirring to combine.
Add soda to last cup of flour.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Great served with lemon sauce or any fruit sauce.
Wonderful just plain!

title: apple pecan cream pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine apple pie filling, brown sugar and cinnamon; stir in pecans.
Spread half the mixture into pie crust; refrigerate remaining mixture.
Place milk and the half and half in a medium size bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture over the apple mixture in pie crust.
Freeze for 2 hours.
Remove from freezer about 10 minutes before serving and garnish with reserved apple mixture.
Add additional Cool Whip on top if desired.
This requires no cooking, is easy and very good!

title: date and nut bread
directions: Mix dates, raisins and baking soda in boiling water.
Set aside to cool.
Beat the eggs and sugar together in a bowl.
Add the date mixture, flour, walnuts and salt.
Mix well.
Grease 4 vegetable cans (1 pound size).
Half fill the cans with batter. The batter will rise over cans while baking.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Boil the water and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add pineapple juice, squeezed orange juice, lemons and bananas.
Cool and freeze overnight in small plastic bowls or jello ring.
Thaw 1 hour before serving.
Add 4 (2 liter) bottles of 7-Up and stir.

title: hot tomato relish
directions: Chop all ingredients through a food chopper and mix with sugar, vinegar and spices.
Cook for 30 minutes until apples are done.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except topping.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Allow cream cheese and butter to soften at room temperature and then blend. Stir in flour. Chill slightly for 1 hour. Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls. Place in tiny, ungreased muffin cups, pressing dough against bottom and sides of cups. Beat together egg, sugar, butter, vanilla and salt until just smooth. Divide half of pecans among pastry lined cups. Add egg mix and top with remaining pecans. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: clara simon's fresh apple cake
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil, vanilla, lemon juice, lemon rind and salt.
Gradually beat in sifted flour, baking soda and cinnamon (mixture will be very thick).
Stir in the apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan (10-inch size). Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Before serving, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine; add onions, mushrooms, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are soft, about 10 minutes.
Add beef and fry until beef loses pink color. Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Bring to simmer.
Stir in cooked macaroni, then cheese.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake uncovered 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: richard's oatmeal cookies(i always have friends ask me for this recipe.)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Stir in by hand.
Stir in pecans, corn flakes and oatmeal.
Drop tablespoon of batter on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven until done.

title: creamy enchiladas(serves 8)
directions: Mix together soup, chilies, 1 cup cheese and sour cream in a saucepan and heat until cheese is melted. Using 1/2 of the soup mixture, spoon soup and ground beef into snack size tortillas. Roll up tortillas and place side by side in long pan with 2-inch sides.
Pour remaining soup mixture over top and sprinkle with rest of cheese. Top with olives.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.

title: angel food cake(serves 16 to 20)
directions: Sift the flour and 1/2 cup sugar together.
Place the egg whites into the large bowl of an electric mixer.
Beat until frothy. Add the cream of tartar and extracts.

Beat until stiff, not dry, then gradually add the remaining 3/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time. Beat well after each addition. Continue beating until the meringue forms stiff peaks and is glossy. Gradually sprinkle the flour-sugar mixture over the meringue, 3 tablespoons at a time, and fold in gently with a rubber spatula to combine.
Quickly but gently push the batter into an ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until the cake springs back when touched with fingers. Remove from oven.
Invert the pan onto a soda bottle and cool upside down for about 1 hour.
When cool, loosen the cake from the sides, bottom and tube of the pan with a long knife and invert onto a platter.
Pass fruit sauce or chocolate sauce, if desired.

title: baked pork chops with dressing
directions: Brown chops on both sides in skillet over medium heat.
Place in greased baking dish.
In mixing bowl, combine bread crumbs, onion, butter, 2 tablespoons water and sage.
Mix well and place over chops.
Combine soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over dressing. Bake uncovered for 45 minutes or until chops are tender at 350°.

title: cheese cake brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degree. Prepare brownie mix as package directed. Reserve 1/2 cup batter. Spread remaining batter evenly in a greased 9 x 13 inch baking pan.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add together all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil and steep the first 2 ingredients.
Boil the 2 cups sugar and 2 cups water 5 minutes until dissolved.
Add the cloves and cinnamon sticks. Strain and add to tea base. Add the orange juice, pineapple juice and ReaLemon.
Pour all in a 1 gallon container and finish filling with water to make a gallon of tea.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Add pineapple juice to rhubarb and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Stir to dissolve and cool.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour into a 2-quart mold and chill.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all together and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Rub butter over oblong glass baking dish.
Spread rest of butter over bread slices.
Fit bread in bottom of baking dish until all edges are covered.
Cut bread to fit.

title: meatballs and potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and cube potatoes.
Put into a large pan (6-quart or larger).
Cover with water.
Salt.
Set aside.

title: rum cake(delicious!!)
directions: Mix all ingredients until moistened.
Place 1/2 cup chopped pecans in bottom of pan and pour mixture into greased Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pralines
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla and pecans. Cook to soft-ball stage. Cool quickly and stir while cooling. Add vanilla and pecans. Drop teaspoonfuls on wax paper. When firm, wrap each one in Saran Wrap.

title: chocolate chip blitz bars
directions: Combine cream cheese, margarine and sugars, mixing until well blended.
Blend in egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Stir in chocolate pieces and nuts.
Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased casserole. Pour melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat balls(makes about 300)
directions: Mix together ground beef and sausage.
Add eggs, milk, water chestnuts, Accent, soy sauce, onions, pepper and bread crumbs.
Mix thoroughly.
Roll into small balls.
Cook in 400° oven for about 20 minutes or until brown.
Put meat balls in crock-pot or covered pan and pour sweet and sour sauce over meat balls.
Simmer.

title: chicken casserole supreme
directions: Stew chicken breasts, adding celery, onion, salt and pepper, if desired, until meat falls off bones.
Cube meat and mix with sour cream and soup.
Put mixture in a 2-quart casserole dish. Mix together stuffing mix, butter and broth.
Put on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: relish
directions: Mix all together and boil 30 minutes.
While boiling, put in jars and seal.

title: ritzy broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt margarine in skillet. Saut crackers in margarine until all margarine is absorbed. Reserve 1/4 cup for topping. Layer broccoli, crackers and cheese in that order in casserole dish until all is used. Top with reserved crackers. Bake in oven until bubbly, about 20 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix well.
Put in tightly closed container.
Use 1 or 2 tablespoons per cup hot water.

title: carrot cake with pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This cake freezes well.
Do not frost if you are going to freeze it.
Thaw and then frost.

title: chicken casserole with pasta
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces and put in casserole.
Add butter,
onion,
peeled
and
diced tomatoes, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Cover
and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender. Add 6 cups
boiling
water and minestra and stir well.
Cover and continue
baking
for
30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve at once with cheese.
Time of preparation: 1 1/2 hours.

title: hamburg patties
directions: Beat egg; add milk and bread crumbs (let soak 1/2 hour).
Add remaining ingredients.
Shape into patties and broil, 8 to 12 minutes on each side.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Put in a
9X 13 greased pan and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes. Sift 1/2 c. powdered sugar and water to make a glaze. Glaze while hot.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar and vanilla until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff peaks form and all sugar is dissolved.
Spread on top of pie sealing to pastry.
Top with coconut if desired.
Bake at 350° 12-15 minutes until meringue is browned.

title: garbage
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and sprinkle with garlic powder (season for taste).
Cut green onion up, keeping the top and bottom apart.
Brown chicken or cook until done.
Add the bottom of the green onions with the chicken.
Add 1 package of chopped broccoli.

title: venison pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place one crust in pie plate.
Saute garlic in skillet with a little oil (chopped onions may also be added).
Add meat and stir.
Leave on heat for one to two minutes, then add Veg-All.
(Any leftover veggies you might have like corn, etc. can be added.)
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stir in a little cornstarch if mixture is too wet.
Pour into crust, add top crust and crimp edges together.
Prick top crust.
Bake until crust becomes golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Melt 1 stick margarine, pour over potatoes and mix.
Add soup mixture, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in oblong casserole dish. Add cheese on top and the cracker crumbs.
Melt 1 stick margarine, pour over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Stir in mixture of flour, baking powder, grated potatoes and salt.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until rounded peaks are formed.
Fold into potato mixture.
Spoon about 2 tablespoons batter for each pancake into hot fat in a skillet. Brown on both sides.
Serve with applesauce.
(Makes about 1 dozen pancakes.)

title: homemade cookie ornaments
directions: Mix together and roll out.
Cut out shapes with cookie cutters. While still soft, punch out hole with pencil or whatever for ribbon.
Dry for a couple of days.
Has a delightful spicy smell for Christmas.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Put sliced apples in baking dish.
Mix other ingredients and spread over apples.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, until done.

title: creole cabbage
directions: Melt the butter in a heavy skillet. Add the cabbage, onion, pepper and seasonings. Cover and cook over low heat until tender, stirring frequently. Add the tomatoes and cook for 10 minutes longer, uncovered.

title: don woods snow ice cream
directions: Combine Milnot, powdered sugar, sugar, egg, vanilla and snow. Mix well quickly.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine eggs, milk and oil together and beat until foamy.
Add baking powder and salt to flour and add gradually to first mixture.
Form into ball and roll out on floured board.
Let dry, then cut in narrow strips.
Add to boiling broth.
Cook slowly until tender, about 45 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix until smooth and creamy.
Serve with crackers, cauliflower, celery, chips, etc.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Set aside.
Combine mayo, sugar and vinegar; add to broccoli mixture.
Stir to coat. Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Crush crackers.
Add 1 stick melted margarine.
Melt cheese and 1/2 stick margarine over very low heat.
Put broccoli into buttered baking dish.
Pour cheese mixture over broccoli; top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until it bubbles.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Cook bacon and place on paper towel.
Saute onions.
Mix eggs well in bowl with whisk, then add milk and cream.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until pie shell is brown and middle is firm.

title: marshmallow fudge sauce
directions: In a
medium saucepan, over low heat, combine marshmallows, milk,
margarine and salt; cook and stir until marshmallows melt and
ingredients are well blended, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla; stir until chips are melted.
Serve
warm
over
ice cream.
Refrigerate leftovers. Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: oven french toast
directions: Place sugar, butter and corn syrup in small pan.
Cook until syrupy.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange cubed bread over syrup.
Beat together eggs, milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Cover pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° to 375°.
Serve with syrup.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and oil. Blend together the sugar, eggs and flour.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hawaiian coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as on package for a sheet cake. When done, poke holes in top with a fork.
Put pineapple, half the cream and 1 can condensed milk after mixed together over the cake.
Put Cool Whip over that, then the coconut.

title: mom's salad
directions: Slice onion, cucumbers, pepper, tomato and cauliflower in pieces.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar, milk, salt and pepper and celery seed until smooth for the dressing.
Stir all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: fresh peach topping
directions: Peel and thinly slice peaches.
Squeeze fresh lemon sparingly over prepared peaches, then evenly sprinkle the sugar over this. Stir in the cherry 7-Up and peach soft drink.
Refrigerate.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar; blend well.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Then add crushed wafers and reduce mixer speed.
Add milk, coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in greased pan.
May be frozen.

title: parmesan garlic bread
directions: Preheat the broiler.
In a blender or small food processor, blend or process the oil and garlic until well combined.
Brush the cut surfaces of the bread with the garlic mixture.

title: sticky buns
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round pan.
Add brown sugar and corn syrup; heat until sugar dissolves.
Sprinkle pecans over sugar mixture.
Place biscuits atop in a single layer.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes. Invert; serve warm.
Makes 10.

title: escalloped cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage; remove hard parts.
Cook in boiling salted water until tender (7 to 10 minutes).
Add grated cheese to medium thick white sauce.
Just before removing from the fire, pour over cabbage in buttered dish.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs and brown in oven.

title: cheeseburger and macaroni
directions: Brown and crumble hamburger.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Prepare macaroni and cheese according to box directions.
Stir in hamburger and shredded cheese.

title: swedish pineapple cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl.
Mix with spoon until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool before icing.
Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: black bean salsa
directions: In a large bowl, mix together black beans, Mexican-style corn, diced tomatoes with green chile peppers, tomatoes and green onion stalks. Garnish with desired amount of cilantro leaves. Chill in the refrigerator at least 8 hours or overnight before serving.

title: italian macaroni pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch pie plate.
Cook and drain macaroni.
Brown ground beef with celery; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine macaroni, eggs, 1/3 cup Parmesan and garlic salt.
Place in pie pan.
Press against bottom and sides to form a crust.
Pour in meat mixture.
Cover with foil and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove foil and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan.

title: flourless peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 - 15 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: grandma theresa's cranberry jello mold
directions: Prepare jello using 2 cups boiling water and 1 cup cold water. Add sugar and
mix
well.
Add
ground cranberries and cut up oranges.
Mix well.
Pour into jello mold.
Chill until firm.

title: banana special
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Press into bottom of pan.
Take banana slices and arrange on crust.
Beat cream cheese in large bowl until smooth.
Gradually add milk and pudding.
Beat until blended.
Spread over banana evenly.
Spread pineapple over pudding mix.
Spoon Cool Whip over pineapple.
Add just a touch of cracker crumbs over top.
Refrigerate for 2 1/2 hours or until ready to serve.

title: soft granola bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Mix brown sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl with a wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Bake just until center is set, but not firm, about 17 to 22 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drizzle evenly with honey glaze.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding with 3 cups milk.
Add Cool Whip; stir, mixing well.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Add a layer of filling, then a layer of graham crackers, then pour the remaining filling on crackers.
Ice graham crackers thinly and place on top of filling.
With remaining icing, smooth over crackers.

title: best ever jam cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Measure spices and salt and add to flour; set aside.
Put soda in buttermilk and add alternately with the flour mixture to the egg mixture, mixing well.
Add vanilla.
Slowly add the preserves, applesauce, raisins and nuts; blend well.
Pour into three greased nine-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cook steak with next 3 ingredients in shortening in covered skillet over high heat for 5 minutes.
Add vegetables, mix well. Cook, covered, over medium heat for 5 minutes longer.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water until smooth.
Add to steak mixture, stirring constantly.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Heat undiluted soup and cheese together.
Add hominy and green chilies.
Pour in baking dish.
Add croutons.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat potato cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into 12 patties.
Brown on both sides in greased frypan over medium heat.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs and crushed bananas.
Combine milk and vinegar to make sour milk.
Next, add flour, salt, baking powder and pecans.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until center is risen.

title: coconut crunchies
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; mix well.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture. Blend in oats, corn flakes and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 13 to 15 minutes in a 325° oven. Good.

title: neighbors chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl.
In a saucepan, put shortening, margarine, water and cocoa; bring to a boil over low heat. Combine with dry ingredients.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Pour Neighbors Chocolate Cake Icing over hot cake.

title: soft chocolate cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, beginning with margarine, sugar, cocoa and eggs, and ending with flour.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased baking pan.
Do not overbake!

title: raspberry vinaigrette salad
directions: Blend oil, vinegar, orange rind, honey, salt and pepper together in screw-top jar; shake vigorously.
Chill.
Combine lettuce, spinach, oranges, kiwi and apples in a large salad bowl, reserving a few kiwi slices for garnish.
Just prior to serving, pour dressing over salad; toss.
Garnish with reserved kiwi. Serves 8.

title: easy sweet twists
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside.
Separate biscuits; roll each into a 9-inch rope.
Dip in butter; coat with sugar mixture.
Twist several times and place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Yields 10 servings.

title: low-fat rice pudding
directions: Add lite whipped topping.

title: vodka slush
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Then add orange juice and lemonade.
Allow to cool at room temperature and add vodka.
Then freeze.
Keep frozen and when ready to use, spoon into a glass and mix with 7-Up.

title: mushroom and egg casserole
directions: In a small saucepan over medium heat, combine soup and milk until hot and smooth.
Set aside.
Mix cheeses together and set aside.
Beat together eggs, milk and spices; set aside.
In a large frying pan melt butter.
Saute mushrooms and onions.
Add beaten eggs and cook until eggs are softly set.
Remove from heat and spoon half of egg mixture into a greased 2 x 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spoon half of soup mixture over eggs and then half of cheese mixture.
Repeat layers.
Sprinkle top with paprika. Bake, uncovered, in a 300° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
If refrigerated, bake 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and syrup in heavy pan until syrup bubbles, then add nuts and cook until candy turns light brown.
Add butter and soda.
Remove from heat.
Stir until butter is melted.
Pour in buttered cookie sheet.
When hard, break into pieces and store in airtight tin.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar, then add oil, walnuts, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon; add to apple mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan in a 350° preheated oven for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or lemon sauce or top with powdered sugar blended with peanut butter.
Add a little hot water if needed.

title: peanut butter smores(kiddie snack)
directions: On a cookie sheet, place crackers, right side up.
Spread on peanut butter and top with 3 or 4 marshmallows.
Bake at 300° until golden brown.

title: frozen lemon cream
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over 1 tablespoon water in large bowl.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: kathy's favorite
directions: Wrap chicken breasts with chipped beef, then bacon. (Toothpick if necessary.)
Mix cream of mushroom soup and sour cream.
Pour over prepared chicken breasts.
Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in covered casserole dish.
Serve over rice.

title: cheese-egg bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir onion in butter until onion is tender; spread in ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches).
Top with egg slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients except bread.
Pour soup mixture over cheese; overlap bread slices, buttered side up, on top of casserole.
Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Set oven control at broil and/or 550°.
Broil 5 inches from heat 1 minute or until bread is toasted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef soup and salad
directions: Boil shank bones in water to cover bones.
Add celery and onion.
Cover and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
When meat is cooked, remove from pot and set aside.
Strain the stock into another pot.
Add cooked pasta.
Shred all of the meat in a bowl. Add sliced red onion, olive oil, vinegar, salt and pepper to taste; mix with romaine lettuce.

title: banana dessert
directions: First Layer:
Put first 3 ingredients together.
Mix until crumbly.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: florida eggplant croquettes
directions: Wash, peel and dice eggplant.
Cook in boiling water until tender, about 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
In a separate bowl, mix the corn meal, flour, sugar, salt, pepper, onions, and drained eggplant.
Lightly beat the eggs and add to the eggplant mixture. Mix well.
Drop the mixture by the spoonful into approximately 1 to 1 1/2 inches of 375° (medium-high temperature) grease.
Cook until brown, turning when needed.
Remove from grease and drain. Yield: 12 medium croquettes.

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, egg yolk and flavoring.
Mix thoroughly. Sift flour again with salt. Add to creamed mixture; blend well. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Form into 1-inch balls. Dip into slightly beaten egg white and roll in decorating sprinkles or coconut.
Place 2-inches apart on greased baking sheet. Dip pecan half into egg white* and place on top, pressing down lightly. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 14 minutes. Remove to rack.
Cool to room temperature.
Store in tightly covered container. Yields 2 dozen.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt and sugar and simmer several minutes in a 13 3/4 x 8 1/2-inch pan.
Layer 1/3 of the sauce and 1/2 of the uncooked noodles.
Add 1 cup of cottage cheese, 1/3 cup of Mozzarella and mild Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce and remaining Mozzarella, Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove foil and let stand 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° in oven.

title: pizzelles
directions: *Do not use more than one cup.

title: low-fat carrot cake
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake in 9-inch cake pan or muffin pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: danish apple bar
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients same as pie crust.
Mix 1 egg yolk in a cup and fill with milk to make 2/3 cup.
Add this to flour mixture.
Divide this in two parts and roll out.
One to cover jelly roll pan.
(Dough is sticky.)
Sprinkle with flour on crust, then put 1-inch thick layer of apples, sliced.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg and sprinkle over apples.
Roll out remaining dough and cover over apples.
Do not make holes in top crust.
Beat egg white stiff and brush top dough.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: overnight pecan rolls
directions: Grease Bundt or angel food pan well.
Place pecans in bottom. Roll frozen rolls in melted butter, then in brown sugar to which cinnamon has been added.
Place rolls on top of pecans in Bundt pan in 2 layers.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix over rolls.
Dribble remaining butter and brown sugar over pudding mix.
Let stand overnight in coolest part of kitchen.
Next morning, bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
(If desired, a few broken pecan pieces can be placed between the 2 layers of rolls.)

title: oven stew
directions: Place all in Dutch oven covered.
Cook at 250° for 4 to 6 hours.

title: spaghetti rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.
Stir in raw rice, water, salt and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and cook until water is absorbed (about 25 minutes).
Stir in cubed cream cheese until it softens.
Combine tomato sauce and chili; pour sauce over rice mixture.
Cover and heat about 5 minutes or until hot.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift sugar, flour, cinnamon, soda and salt together.
In another bowl, mix the eggs, oil, bananas, pineapple, vanilla and nuts.
Pour second mixture over the first and stir.
Do not beat. Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cake cool completely. Ice with cream cheese icing.

title: tamale style stuffed peppers
directions: Split peppers lengthwise.
Remove and discard seeds and veins. Drop in pan of boiling water. When water returns to boil, drain peppers.
Put tomatoes in saucepan and cook about 3 minutes, stirring and breaking up lumps. Add corn meal; stir constantly. Let cook over low heat about 10 minutes. Stir often to prevent lumps.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in saucepan.
Add onion and garlic. Stir until onion wilts.
Add beef and chop with heavy metal spoon. Add the spices, salt and pepper.
Add tomato and corn meal mixture.
Blend well. Place mixture in the pepper halves. Sprinkle with the grated Cheddar cheese. Bake 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven, uncovered.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Grate cheese.
Have cheese and margarine at room temperature; cream together thoroughly.
Gradually add flour, red pepper and salt.
Make 3 rolls and roll in waxed paper; chill several hours, slice and top with pecan half.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add yeast to water.
Add oil and buttermilk.
Add all this to dry ingredients and knead until smooth.
Store in refrigerator in tight container, allowing room for bread to rise.
Pinch off as much as needed at a time.
Will keep up to 2 weeks in the refrigerator.
Bake 15 minutes at 400° to 425° or let rise 30 minutes and then bake.
Good either way!

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: On low heat, break candy bar up and melt.
Remove from heat and let slightly cool.
Fold in Cool Whip and coffee.
Stir well.
Pour in pie crust and freeze at least 1 hour before serving.
Very rich! Makes 8 to 10 slices.

title: marshmallow pops
directions: You will need 18 to 20 wooden sticks.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Roll in balls.
Press with fork and bake at 350°.

title: shrimp lori
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Place remaining ingredients in a large frypan or wok.
Toss together for 5 to 8 minutes; add soup mix.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes, until heated through.
Serve over rice; garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix peanuts, sugar and syrup in heavy, oversize saucepan. Boil until honey-colored, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in baking powder, stirring briskly.
Mixture will almost double in bulk.

title: red russian salad dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients on low speed in food processor; beat 20 minutes.

title: oven chicken supreme
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, butter and paprika.
Spread on chicken with spatula.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place skin side up in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add chopped onion, then milk and egg.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot grease.
When done, they will float.
Put on paper towel to drain.

title: cheddar cheese and asparagus soup
directions: Melt butter in heavy, medium size saucepan over medium heat. Add asparagus and garlic; saute, stirring occasionally, about 5 minutes.
Gradually blend in flour; cook, stirring constantly, 3 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Gradually stir in 1 cup milk and the cheese; cook, stirring constantly until cheese is melted.
Stir in remaining milk, salt and pepper.
Stir just until hot.
Remove garlic before serving.

title: honey-glazed baked pears
directions: Rinse and peel pears.
Cut into halves.
Remove cores. Lightly grease an ovenproof plate.
Place pear halves on plate, cut side down.
Squeeze juice from lemon.
Melt butter.
Brush pear halves with lemon juice.
Drizzle with
melted butter. Drizzle honey over pears and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes, basting with pan juices from time to time.
Add cream or half and half. Bake another 2 to 4 minutes. Remove from oven and garnish with mint leaves.
Serve warm.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
