directions: In a large soup kettle, combine the water, the carrots, celery and onion. Put in the bouillon granules and let the vegetables simmer for 5 minutes, then add the chicken and broth. Let them cook for another 5 minutes. Then add the noodles and cook until the vegetables and the noodles are tender. Do not overcook the soup or you will have mushy noodles.

title: strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix cheese and milk with mixer.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour in crust and let refrigerate until firm.
Pour on strawberries as desired.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix potato, vanilla, egg and brown sugar together with enough cream to make a good mixture.
Add coconut and mix well.
Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with marshmallows.
Return to oven to brown.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Heat a lightly greased 8-inch cast-iron skillet in a 400 degrees oven.
Combine cornmeal and remaining ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Remove prepared skillet from oven and spoon batter into skillet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: banana tea bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake 1 hour in slow 300° oven.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in egg yolks until well blended.
Beat in sour cream, almond extract and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking soda together.
Beat flour mixture into batter, one cup at a time.
Blend well.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.

title: jam fruit cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour and all dry ingredients together.
Then the rest of the ingredients, add to this mixture.
Put into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bernice's chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine Pillsbury pie crust mix with flour and just enough water to moisten the mixture. Roll out tissue paper thin on a floured paper. Cut into strips or squares and drop in chicken broth that has been brought to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat and carefully stir in the deboned chicken.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Spread dry rice in a greased baking dish. Pour mixed liquids over rice.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Sprinkle with Lipton onion soup mix. Bake at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli. Layer broccoli, cheese and sauce in casserole. Top with croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 3 cheese chicken bake
directions: In skillet, saute onion and pepper in butter until tender. Stir in undiluted soup and drained mushrooms and pimentos.
Add basil. In an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan, mix together noodles, chicken, Ricotta and Cheddar.
Pour sauce mix over and top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: nonie's lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat; add spaghetti sauce and mix. Boil lasagna noodles until tender; drain. Layer noodles, meat mixture, and both cheeses. The final layer should be cheese. Bake at 350° until completely heated through.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into container and freeze.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: In a large bowl combine brown sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add milk.
Beat 30 seconds. Stir in rhubarb and blend well.

title: 1000 island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together real good and let set a while.

title: foil baked chicken
directions: In bowl, blend together all ingredients except chicken.
Dip chicken in sauce.
Divide chicken in 4 to 6 serving-size portions, placing each serving on separate piece of heavy foil.
Pour about 1 teaspoon sauce over each portion of chicken; seal foil securely. Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Open foil packets; brush with remaining sauce.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon swirl
directions: Use about 1/3 of refrigerator dough.
Roll out dough into a 12 x 7-inch oblong pan.
Spread surface with melted butter
with pastry brush.
Sprinkle with the sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up as for cinnamon rolls.
Cut into 12 slices; place with a little space between in greased 9-inch round pan.
Cover; let rise until light (25 to 35 minutes).
Bake until golden brown; remove from pan.
If desired, top with icing.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine water, butter and salt in saucepan, bring to boil. Stir in rice, cover and set off heat.
Let stand 5 minutes, fluff with fork and let cool.
Stir in pineapple, marshmallows, coconut and cherries.
Fold in Cool Whip, cover, chill about 1 hour. Serves 8.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Pour oil over flour and salt.
Mix and roll into a ball. Divide into 2 parts for the crust.
Roll between wax paper. Remove wax paper and put in pie pan.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Bake beef in a 350° oven until very tender. Add 1/2 cup water to pan when first put in oven.
Flake meat when done.
In frypan, add onion and pepper. Saute until slightly done.
Add ketchup, sauce, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and chili powder. Add the flaked meat and juices.
Simmer 40 minutes. Serve on a hamburger roll.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add egg; blend.
Add dry ingredients and melted butter; mix well.
Spoon mixture into well-greased muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: chicken barley soup, mexican style
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven or soup pot, combine chicken breast, broth and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Additional broth may need to be added if soup becomes too thick upon standing.

title: black forrest cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Don't use a mixer, this will crush the cherries.
Pour into a 9 by 13-inch greased and floured pan or a greased bunt pan.
Bake at 350 degrees 40 - 45 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Cook in large pot until amber in color.
Do not stir.
Pour over 2-quarts popped corn; stir well.
Place in pans to cool. Break into pieces.

title: non-toxic play dough
directions: Mix the salt, flour and cream of tartar, then add the water, oil and coloring.
Cook on medium heat until dough is consistency of thick mashed potatoes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Let cool slightly.
Store in plastic bag.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Melt butter in skillet; saute celery and onion until tender, about 3 minutes.
In large mixing bowl, combine cornbread, toasted bread slices, cooked celery and onions, sage and black pepper. Stir broth and eggs into cornbread mixture; blend well.
Pour into prepared baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 10 servings.

title: candy cane creams
directions: Melt almond (white chocolate) bark and mix in crushed candy canes, peppermint flavoring and red food coloring until well blended.
Spread onto wax paper covered cookie sheet and refrigerate until hardened.
Break or cut into bite size pieces and serve.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar together.
Then mix eggs and vanilla.
Add all other ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoonful on an ungreased baking sheet, approximately 2-inches apart.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 375° oven.
Cool on wire racks.

title: heloise's olive nut spread
directions: Mash softened cream cheese with a fork.
Add mayonnaise. Blend well.
Stir in pecans, olives, juice and dash of pepper. Mix well.
Refrigerate.
It will be firmer and of spreading consistency after it is refrigerated for a few hours.
Serve spread with party rye bread.
Makes 2 cups.

title: rice and veggie salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions until all water is absorbed. Cool rice.
Add veggies to cooled rice. Toss with salad dressing and chill for 12 hours.

title: apple delight
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Blend in oil.
Mix flour, salt, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add apples and nuts.
Pour in ungreased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: chili rolls
directions: Cut slit in side of each roll (do not cut all the way through). Scoop out insides.
Set aside.
Brown beef, onion and garlic in skillet.
Add chili sauce, tomato sauce, salt, black pepper and chili powder.
Simmer, stirring for 10 minutes.
Cut cheese into chunks.
Stir into meat mixture and heat until almost melted.
Fill rolls with chili mixture.
Wrap each in foil.
Heat at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: I usually take all skin and fat off chicken.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then shake in a bag containing crushed corn flakes and seasonings.
Bake at 350° in 13 x 9-inch pan for 50 minutes or until done.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Sift together 3 cups flour, baking soda and milk.
Mix alternately with liquid mixture.
Add walnut flavoring and nuts.
Pour immediately into ungreased tube pan, or 3 loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° on lowest rack for 30 minutes.
Move to second rack and finish baking.
Bake 1 hour or longer.
Cool for 3 hours.

title: baked donuts
directions: Stir together dry ingredients. Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat for 1 minute with an electric mixer. Add oil/applesauce and mix for another minute. Best if using the black donut pans; spray with Pam. Pour batter into each mold about 1/2 full. Bake in a preheated 400° oven for approximately 10 minutes or until golden. Cool on rack.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook zucchini 1/2 hour.
Saute grated leeks in butter until wilted.
Add chicken stock and zucchini.
Add cut up package of cream cheese and grated cheese.
Serve hot or cold.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating after each.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to sugar mixture; alternate with 1 cup buttermilk.
Add vinegar and soda.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pasta salad(with lemon, thyme and prosciutto)
directions: Cook pasta in 4 qt. water with 1 Tbsp. salt, until al dente. Drain and rinse under cool water.
Drain again.
Transfer pasta to a shallow serving platter.
Toss with olive oil.
Add lemon peel, lemon juice, thyme, parsley, garlic, Prosciutto, remaining salt, pepper hot sauce and mix thoroughly.
Taste and adjust seasoning if needed.
To serve; garnish with sprigs of thyme. Makes 6 - 8 servings.

title: noodles and mushroom soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook noodles until done. Drain. Add mushroom soup and milk. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate peppermint cookie twists
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine, shortening, powdered sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cocoa and salt.
Knead a level tablespoonful of dough with hands until right consistency for molding.
Roll into pencil-like strip, about 9 inches long, on a lightly floured board.
Twist into pretzel shape on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining dough.
Bake until set, about 9 minutes.
Let stand 1 to 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheet; cool.
Dip tops of cookies into Chocolate Glaze (follows). Sprinkle with peppermint candy.

title: crunch crust(for those who can't roll out pie crust.)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients with a fork and spread into oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Stir baked mixture with a spoon.
While still warm, press firmly into 9-inch pie pan.
Cool.

title: artichoke mushroom casserole
directions: Mix together and place into a heavy, oiled casserole baking dish. Top with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, grated and 1 cup sharp Cheddar cheese, grated. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Test for doneness with a knife. Serves 6.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix well.
I use a blender.
If you would like to make sugar free, use 12 packages of Sweet 'N Low.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
Work with spoon the shortening until soft.
Add sugar gradually, mixing well after each addition!
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Beat well after each addition.
Pour 1/3 of batter into one layer pan.
Set side. To remaining batter, add cinnamon, ground cloves and allspice. Beat well.
Fold in raisins and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Turn batter into two remaining pans.
Bake 3 layers in 375° oven, about 35 minutes.

title: hearty chef's salad
directions: Break lettuce into bowl.
Add remaining vegetables.
Toss well with dressing.
Cut meat into strips.
Top lettuce mixture with meat, cheese strips and eggs.
Serve with extra dressing.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pepper pot
directions: In large Dutch oven slowly brown veal shanks and sausage and stew in oil.
Remove sausage, cool, slice and refrigerate.
In Dutch oven, add next 7 ingredients.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until tender (1 1/2 hours).
Remove shanks from stock, cool and skim off fat.
Remove veal from bones and cube.
In large skillet, saute red onion and celery in margarine 10 minutes. Add peppers and saute 5 minutes.
In Dutch oven, bring stock to boil.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook 10 minutes. Add sauteed vegetables, veal and sausage.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: dry milk ost-kaka(swedish cheesecake)
directions: Mix Carnation dry milk and warm water.
Add flour mixed with enough cold water to make a smooth paste.
Stir mixture into warm milk and then add 1 tablet of Rennet.
Stir well.
Let stand in warm area for at least 45 minutes.
Then drain off the whey (about 3 cups).

title: strawberry pie
directions: Broil until thick.
Let cool.
Add 1 quart strawberries.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing lightly. Place in a greased 1 1/2 to 2 quart casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: no fool pie
directions: Preheat oven
to
Using low heat, melt butter in small saucepan, stirring constantly.
Transfer butter to 8 or 9-inch long baking dish and set aside for a moment.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and butter.
Grease shallow, 8-inch square pan.
Fill bottom of pan with sliced apples.
Put topping over apples.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for approximately 25 minutes.
Serve with ice cream!

title: fried burritos
directions: Heat mixture over medium heat.
Place meat mixture on edge of tortilla.
Fold in sides.
Roll up and fry on both sides in medium hot oil.
Tortillas should be at room temperature to avoid cracking.
Makes about 20 burritos.

title: marinated onion salad
directions: Slice onions; separate into rings.
Combine water, sugar and vinegar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over onions.
Cover and chill at least 3 to 4 hours; drain.
Stir in mayonnaise and celery seed.
Good served on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken mushroom casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers, also mushrooms if using fresh ones, in skillet until done.
Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rich chocolate and lemon frosting
directions: Melt together chocolate and butter. Add salt and cool. Add egg, flavoring and sugar.
Blend until smooth and creamy.
Mix in nuts.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups or enough to cover sides and top of 10-inch tube cake.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Place flour in a 9-inch pie pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over flour.
Press into place.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.

title: beer bread(whoa!)
directions: Place flour and sugar in bowl.
Pour beer over dry ingredients and stir until sticky.
Place in greased loaf pan.
Pour 1/3 of melted margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pour 1/3 more margarine over bread and cook 20 minutes more.
Pour last 1/3 margarine over loaf; bake 20 minutes.
Cool and slice.
Serve with butter and honey.

title: rocky roads
directions: In top of double boiler, over boiling water, melt chocolate morsels with sweetened condensed milk and butter; remove from heat.
In a large bowl, combine peanuts and marshmallows; fold in the chocolate mixture.
Spread in wax paper-lined 13 x 9-inch pan. Chill 2 hours or until set.
Remove from pan, peel off the wax paper and cut into squares.
Cover and store at room temperature. Yields 40.

title: apple smoked cheddar tea sandwiches
directions: Combine mayonnaise or cream cheese, curry powder and chutney. Mix well and divide between bread slices.
Spread butter on the outside surface of bread.
Heat nonstick skillet.
Put half of cheese on two bread slices; divide and layer with apple slices overlapping top with watercress leaves, then layer with remaining cheese.
Top with remaining slices of bread and press together. Place in warmed skillet.
Put butter on top side while in skillet. Cook about 4 minutes per side to brown, turning carefully.
Cut in quarters to serve.

title: pecan rolls
directions: Mix brown sugar and melted butter.
Put in 18 muffin tins. Add teaspoon cold water to each.
Layer bottom of tin with pecan halves.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening or margarine.
Add slightly beaten eggs and milk all at the same time.
Beat until blended.
Turn out on slightly floured board and knead 8 or 10 times.
Roll into rectangle. Brush with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar mixture. Roll as you would a jelly roll and cut in 3/4-inch slices.
Put in muffin tins on top of pecans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Turn upside down immediately.
Makes 18.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread.
Let cool and crumble in large bowl.
Add other ingredients and blend.
Serve with pinto beans.
Serves four.

title: jello salad
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients together in pan; cook to boiling. Cool.
Add the drained Mandarin oranges and crushed pineapple, then fold in the Cool Whip.

title: okra salad
directions: Fry okra according to package directions; drain and allow to cool completely. In a large bowl, combine okra with onions, tomatoes and crumbled bacon; mix gently. Add mixture of oil, sugar and vinegar; toss to coat. Chill until ready to serve.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with crackers cooked in melted butter and poppy seed.
Cook until hot and bubbly.

title: baked scallops
directions: Mix crumbs and spices together.
Melt butter in 8 x 8 pyrex baking dish.
Wash scallops in cold water, pat dry.
Place in pyrex dish with butter in it, turn the scallops so that all sizes are covered with butter, sprinkle with crumbs mixture.
Pour 1/2 c. milk over this and place in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: macaroni-chipped beef casserole
directions: Stir soup to make a creamy consistency.
Add milk, cheese, onion powder, uncooked macaroni, dried beef and mushrooms.
Fold in eggs.
Turn into buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Store, covered, in refrigerator at least 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin dump cake
directions: Mix pumpkin.
Pour into baking dish, 13 x 9-inch.
Sprinkle dry yellow cake mix over top.
Slice 1 1/2 sticks margarine; dot on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with be light brown.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Stir flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large bowl, beat butter and shortening until butter is soft.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide in half.

title: ten minute tetrazzini
directions: Blend the jar of chicken gravy, milk, Parmesan cheese and chicken together.
Heat slowly, stirring occasionally.
Fold in 2 cups spaghetti.
Heat until hot.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: sweet potato nut balls
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, orange juice and sugar. Blend well. Shape into 12 sweet potato balls. Insert 1 large marshmallow inside each ball. Roll the sweet potato balls in chopped pecans. Place on a cookie sheet and heat in a 350° oven 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Split Twinkies lengthwise and place in a single layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crushed pineapple with juice.
Slice bananas and cover the pineapple layer.
Spread whipped topping over bananas.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: crumb cake
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Save 1/2 cup of this mixture to sprinkle on cake before baking.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Top with mixture.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: pecan brittle
directions: Grease 2 qt. glass measuring bowl, cook sugar, syrup and salt on high in microwave 2-3 minutes (until boiling). Cook 4 minutes more, stir in nuts, oleo and vanilla. cook 2 minutes. Immediately stir in baking soda until light and foamy. Quickly pour onto greased cookie sheet, spread with spoon. Cool, break into pieces.

title: country cracker and chip dip
directions: In a double boiler or microwave, boil eggs, sugar and vinegar until thick.
Then add remaining ingredients and mix.
Chill and serve.
Makes a nice large batch of dip.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all except cheese, almonds and potato chips.
Place in a large rectangular dish.
Top with cheese first, then potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigearator.
Bake in 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Great for a luncheon.

title: nippy beets
directions: Blend and heat.
Spoon over cooked, drained baby beets; stir to glaze.

title: peanut patties
directions: Parch 2 cups of peanuts.
Boil other ingredients to soft ball stage.
Add peanuts and return to soft ball stage by boiling. Remove from heat and add 1 cup powdered sugar and dash of red food coloring.
Drop by large tablespoon on waxed paper.
Yield: 40 small patties.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a pie crust.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Beat egg whites, sweetened with 6 tablespoons sugar.
Top pie with egg whites.
Put back in oven until brown.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve sugar in very hot water.
Add Jell-O and mix well. In another container add gelatin into cold water.
Add lemon juice.
Blend well and add to Jell-O mixture.
Mix well and pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and refrigerate.
When set, cut into cubes for tiny fingers.

title: corn casserole - ii
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package. Mix undrained corn, celery soup, butter and 1 cup of cheese into rice. Pour into casserole dish and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix the mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over salad just before serving. Keeps well.
Makes 10 servings.

title: soy marinade
directions: Mix all
ingredients; add brisket.
Marinate at least 1 day and night
and turn frequently.
To cook:
wrap brisket in heavy-duty foil and cook in marinade at 325°.

title: world's best cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter and sugar.	Add egg and beat well.	Add salad
oil;
beat
well.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add
to
creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, oats, cornflakes, coconut and nuts.
Drop from end of teaspoon onto a baking sheet
and
press
lightly with a fork. Bake about 12 minutes.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix well with salad dressing and chill.

title: german chocolate pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Melt in double boiler the margarine and chocolate. Cool.
Beat eggs, sugar and flour together.
Add melted mixture.
Now add vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and top with 1/4 pint whipped cream.

title: rich hot rolls
directions: Scald milk.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast on warm water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour to milk mixture.
Beat with electric mixer at low speed 1 minute.
Beat in eggs and yeast.
Gradually stir in enough flour, a little at a time, to make soft dough that leaves side of bowl. Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth (5 to 8 minutes).
Place in greased bowl.
Turn to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down and turn onto board.
Divide in half and shape as desired.
Brush top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ritzy pie crust
directions: Sift flour and add salt.
Cut in Crisco until crumbly.
Add ice water.
Stir with a fork (or spoon) and finish mixing with hand until smooth.
Chill.
Roll out on lightly floured board. Fit into pans and bake according to pie directions.
Bake pastry shell 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
This pastry can be stored several days in refrigerator and even frozen.

title: poppy seed wine cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add sherry and oil.
Beat in eggs, 1 at a time.
Turn batter into a 12-cup greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes before putting on a plate. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: maple coleslaw
directions: Whisk together the mayonnaise, maple syrup, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour the dressing over the salad and toss to coat.
Chill for 2 hours before serving. Makes 6 to 8 cups.

title: easy macaroons
directions: Mix ingredients together; add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes or until delicate brown.
Remove from pan at once and cool on rack. Yields 30.

title: green beans in mushroom sauce(my mama's recipe)
directions: Make a sauce of butter, flour and mushroom soup.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Pour over beans and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Cook at 350° until bubbly and crumbs are lightly browned.

title: homemade meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape meat into balls.
Brown meatballs in skillet.
Drain grease and add to Italian Pasta Sauce (see recipe).
Cook slowly for about 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta.

title: nettie's zucchini pie
directions: Peel and cut large zucchini; remove seeds.
Cut in cubes and cook until tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie pan lined with crust.
Put top crust on.
Cut vent slits in crust.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Turn down heat to 350° and finish baking until golden brown, about 20 or 25 minutes longer.

title: pecan snowballs
directions: Cream oleo, vanilla and sugar together until fluffy.
Add salt and flour; mix and add pecans.
Mix well.
Shape in 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil over medium-high heat in a heavy kettle; add rice and next 7 ingredients.
Cook until rice is browned, stirring often.
Stir in water and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and cook 25 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add other 4 ingredients and put on greased foil by the teaspoonful. Bake for 1 hour at 250°. Let set in oven until cool. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put apples and sugar in buttered baking dish, sprinkled with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Mix butter, brown sugar and flour until resembles coarse meal.
Sprinkle over apples and bake slowly at 375° for 1 hour.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix together and use as needed.

title: berry cream coffee cake
directions: Combine.
Drizzle over top while still hot.

title: jello cheese cake
directions: Chill bowl, beaters and milk 8 hours or overnight.
Have oleo and cream cheese at room temperature.
Make crust by mixing graham crackers, powdered sugar and oleo until crumbly.
Save 1/2 cup crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining crumb mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: rose's fudge
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Add melted chocolate.
Add vanilla, salt and nuts.
Butter pan and pack in fudge. Refrigerate.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Blend cream
cheese and mayonnaise (salad dressing such as Miracle Whip light	may
be
used, as well as low-fat cream cheese).
Spread mixture
evenly over the pizza crusts. Sprinkle other ingredients
evenly
over
the cream cheese mixture, pressing them down lightly.
Chill and cut into 2-inch squares to serve.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Stir in 4 egg yolks and milk; blend well.
Cook, stirring until thickened. Reduce heat.
Add raisins and cook 5 minutes more.
Add vanilla. Spread small amount in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with a layer of wafers, top with 1/3 of sliced bananas, then 1/3 of custard.
Repeat twice, ending with custard.
Beat egg whites with remaining sugar.
Spoon on top of pudding.
Bake at 425° until meringue browns.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix cooked squash with other ingredients except for the oleo and stuffing mix.
Melt oleo and mix with stuffing mix.
Alternate layers of squash mixture and stuffing mixture.
Save enough stuffing mixture to put on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: moore's drugstore pintos
directions: On any Tuesday or Thursday, call Robert Robinson around 11:00 a.m. and say "Beans".
Be prepared to leave in 15 minutes.
Go to Moore's Drugstore and order pinto beans with not too much juice and not too many beans so as to leave room for cornbread, onions and pepper relish.
Either chop Robert's homemade peppers or use Buddy and Dean Travis' hot pepper relish.
(Not for those who don't like it hot.)
Place peppers, onion and 1/2 piece of cornbread, crumbled, into pintos.
Stir slightly.
Best if eaten with an egg-olive sandwich, no slaw and lots of cold sweet tea with plenty of good friends.

title: dill and lemon flounder bake(serves 6; under 100 calories)
directions: Combine 1 teaspoon dill with lemon peel and black pepper.
Rub into both sides of each fillet.
Roll up fillets from narrow ends; secure with toothpicks, if needed.
Place in shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine water, vermouth, lemon juice and remaining dill.
Pour sauce over fish.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish tests done when flaked with fork.
Serve with sauce spooned over fish.
Contains 49 calories per serving.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, eggs and sugar.
Add the rest.
Roll in sugar and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Real butter is the secret!

title: pumpkin cranberry bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, soda, nutmeg and ginger; set aside. Combine (cream together) sugar, pumpkin, eggs and oil. Stir well. Add flour mixture until moistened. Fold in chopped cranberries. Pour into greased pans, two 9 x 5 or you can use the small pans which it makes 6 small pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until done.

title: jelly roll
directions: Bake at 375° approximately 20 minutes.
Turn top side down onto a towel or breadboard that has been covered with confectioners sugar.
Roll up in towel and let set until cool.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cream all ingredients together and spread over crackers or small slices of bread.
Place very thin slice of cucumber on top and sprinkle with dill.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Heat olive oil and saute the paprika or sofrito.
If using ground annatto, add when you add the water.
Add tomato sauce. Cook until the mixture comes to a boil, about 1 minute.
Add the chicken and cook until it turns white, then add the rice.
Mix well with the other ingredients.
If you are using ground annatto, dissolve the annatto and salt in the water.
Pour the water mixture into the pan with the rice.
Cook on medium low, until the liquid has evaporated.
Cover and cook until the rice is tender, 15 -20 minutes.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat after each. Add vanilla wafers alternately with milk. Add coconut and pecans. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Cut up broccoli and add other ingredients.

title: cabbage rolls(my dad's)
directions: Put cabbage head in boiling water to wilt.
Separate leaves. Combine ingredients.
Place filling in cabbage leaf and pin with toothpicks.
Place in deep pan and pour 1 can stewed tomatoes and 1 can tomato sauce over rolls.
Cook over low to medium heat, covered, 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Cut into bite size pieces and put in	oblong baking dish.
Mix broth and soup until smooth. Pour over chicken.

title: frozen lemon salad
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix in Rice Krispies and sugar.
Pat mixture into pan and bake at 300° for 12 minutes. Drain fruit cocktail and mix with lemon juice, condensed milk and lemon pie filling.
Spread on baked Rice Krispies mixture.
Freeze for 4 hours.
Serve with any whipped topping.

title: mincemeat squares
directions: Cream together the margarine and brown sugar.
Add mincemeat, eggs and flavoring.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; add to mincemeat mixture and mix thoroughly.
Add chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Serves 12 to 15.

title: ham linguine florentine
directions: In a heavy 12-inch skillet, brown almonds over medium heat about 5 minutes or until golden.
Remove from skillet; set aside.

title: strawberry-yogurt salad
directions: Heat pineapple and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved; let cool.
Add yogurt, Cool Whip and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salted water and drain.
Brown ground beef and season with salt and pepper.
Put in casserole dish in alternate layers, starting with noodles, then beef, then cheese, then soup, repeating until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. May be garnished with parsley.

title: baked sweet onions (vidalias)
directions: Slice onions; cut each slice in half.
Saute onions in 1/4 cup butter in a Dutch oven until crisp-tender; spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: nel's chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or a Bundt prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chinese chews
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients and stir in dates, nuts and eggs.
Pour into greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in moderate oven about 15 minutes.
Cut while warm.
Cool and remove.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pot pie
directions: Beat egg in milk.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture. Roll thin and cut in squares. Drop in broth until done.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Slice end off bread (1 to 1 1/2-inches) and pull out part of center to make room for stuffing.
Saute meat, onion and bell pepper.
Stir in broccoli and Cheez Whiz.
Spoon mixture into bread and put bread back together.
Wrap each in foil.
Heat at 300° until warmed.
Freezes well.
Let thaw and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat pumpkin mixture until smooth, then pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix yellow cake mix and margarine until like pie crust. Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350°.
When about half done, sprinkle with the chopped nuts and continue baking.
(If you add the nuts at the start of baking, they will get too brown.)

title: chicken pie
directions: Place cooked and cut up chicken into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add carrots and potatoes over chicken.
Mix soup and broth; pour over mixture in pan.
In another bowl, melt margarine.
Add flour and milk, mixed thoroughly, and spoon over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered with foil.
Remove foil to brown.

title: joyce's graham cracker cake
directions: Into large mixing bowl, cream butter, eggs, vanilla and milk. Add baking powder, salt, graham cracker crumbs, sugar, drained pineapple, coconut and walnuts.
Mix together for about 2 minutes. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cake will be very moist.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole, place alternating layers of oysters with liquid and crackers, dotting each layer with butter and sprinkling with pepper.
Add milk until liquid almost reaches top of casserole.
Dot with remaining margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° until browned, 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 6 generous servings.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Preheat oven at 425°.
Lightly oil iron skillet or heavy baking pan and heat in oven.
Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites, buttermilk and oil; add to dry ingredients.
Stir lightly with wooden spoon.
Pour batter into preheated skillet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings, 160 calories per serving.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Boil and cut up chicken. Pour noodles in bottom of a large casserole. Combine rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour this over the noodles.
Top with rest of noodles.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: roast
directions: Put roast in roasting pan, season with salt, pepper, and garlic. Cut onion, green onions, and bell peppers up and place on roast. Fill pot up almost halfway with water. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: riverbank stew
directions: Cut up corned beef and add tomatoes and beans.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Serve with onions and cornbread.

title: cinnamon flop
directions: Mix together.
Put in 2 pie or cake pans.
Dot with 1 tablespoon margarine in small pieces.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar together 3 times. Cream butter and add well beaten egg.
Add milk and mix all together.
Spread in a pan, about 3/8-inch thick.
Cover with apples (peeled, cored and sliced).
Lay in rows, overlapping each other.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve while still warm.

title: margaret's divinity
directions: Stir sugar, corn syrup and water over low heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook, without stirring, to 260°.
In mixing bowl beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Continue beating while pouring hot syrup in a thin stream into egg whites.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture holds it shape and becomes slightly dull.
Fold in nuts.
Drop mixture from tip of buttered spoon on waxed paper.

title: one bowl applesauce cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add all the rest and beat together well.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Do toothpick test after 35 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter ritz crackers cookies
directions: Put peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers and dip in melted bulk milk chocolate until completely covered.
Place on wax paper until dry.

title: trevin's snacks on a stick
directions: Place a large flour tortilla on a paper towel.
Microwave on High for 30 seconds or until soft.
Cool.
Fold tortilla into quarters.
With scissors, cut out small pieces; unfold and set aside.
Place another tortilla on plate and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Top with other tortilla.
Microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds or until cheese melts.
Cut in quarters and serve with salsa.

title: the best split pea soup
directions: Heat peas and water to boiling; boil gently 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until peas are very soft.
Remove bone; trim meat from bone and add to soup.
If desired thin with milk or water; season to taste.
Makes 6 cups. You can substitute 1 pound ham shank or ham hocks for ham bone.

title: maizie's almond tea bread
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately to ingredients the milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease and flour 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Times may vary according to pan size.

title: marg's zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325° and grease two loaf pans (8-inch).
Mix eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini until well blended.
Fold in dry ingredients including nuts.
Turn batter into baking pans. Bake approximately 1 hour.

title: chicken-wild rice casserole
directions: Saut celery, onion and green pepper in butter.
Cook celery and onion down until all celery juice has evaporated.
Cook wild rice in chicken broth.
Add cooked white rice.
Mix all ingredients and put in a casserole dish.
Be generous with almonds on top. Bake in 325° oven about an hour.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients 24 hours in advance of serving. Refrigerate.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift together first 7 ingredients.
In a large bowl mix Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add prunes.
Add sifted flour mixture alternately with 1 cup buttermilk.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into two 9-inch layer cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Frost with Buttermilk Icing.

title: savory apple pork chops
directions: In
a skillet coated with vegetable spray, brown chops on both sides.
Drain off any fat.
Top chops with apple slices, raisins and lemon rind.
Pour apple juices over top.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes until tender.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix first 5 ingredients thoroughly.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts (optional) and chocolate chips. Drop rounded teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until delicately brown.	Slightly cool before taking off of pan.
Yield:
4 to 5 dozen (2-inch) cookies.

title: layered salad
directions: Let set for 8 to 12 hours.

title: baked vidalia onions("serve in place of baked potatoes!")
directions: You will need 2 to 3 feet of heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: mae's vlasic dill pickles
directions: Pour all liquid off pickles and rinse.
Add sugar.
Shake pickles and sugar together and let juice form.

title: hot dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in jar with 1 head of dill, 1 hot pepper and 1 clove garlic on top and bottom of jar.
Boil water, vinegar and salt; pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: fresh fruit coconut dessert
directions: Layer half the peaches, bananas and strawberries in a serving bowl.
Top with half of the coconut; repeat.
Chill.

title: sweet potato chips
directions: Forget greasy potato chips.
A new treat has 40 calories and no fat at all.
Sprinkle slices of sweet potatoes with salt, cinnamon, sugar or chili powder and pop them in a microwave for four or five minutes on High.
Yum.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Combine beef, onion, salt and pepper; cook over medium heat until meat is brown.
Drain.
Add potatoes and water.
Cover and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: baked cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower until tender.
Place in 8-inch glass dish. Cover with slices of yellow American cheese.
Crumble on Ritz crackers.
Drizzle melted margarine over crackers.
Bake uncovered 30 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Drain oysters; remove liquor.
Coarsely crush wafers by hand.
Melt 1/2 cup butter; combine with oyster liquor and cream.
Butter a 7 x 7-inch casserole dish and line bottom with 1 cup crushed crackers.
Lay one layer of oysters over crackers.
Drizzle 1/3 of cream mixture over oysters. Sprinkle lightly with nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Cover oysters with 1 cup crushed crackers.
Put second layer of oysters on crackers; repeat with 1/3 of cream mixture.
Once again, season.
Top with final cup crushed crackers; drizzle remaining cream mixture over all.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cake mix, margarine and nuts. Pour into a greased baking pan. Sprinkle cake mix on top; drizzle margarine over the cake mix. Top with chopped nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour only.

title: linguine salad
directions: Follow directions on box for cooking noodles.
Chop onions, tomatoes and the meat of your choice.
Zucchini should be thinly sliced.
In a large bowl, put in the noodles and add remaining ingredients.
Toss well.
Ready to serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups and water.
Stir in rice.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan. Place chicken on top.
Cook 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place potato slices in greased casserole dish.
Add onions. Then spread soup, water and pimento over potatoes.
Add floured pork chops on top.
Bake 45 minutes in 400° oven.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix all other ingredients.
Fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until browned.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add taco seasoning. Mix and let cool.
Add the hamburger mixture to the remaining ingredients; mix together and serve.

title: love punch
directions: Puree strawberries in blender.
Blend in orange juice.
Divide into 6 to 8 glasses.
Fill to the tops with ginger ale.

title: green beans and chourico
directions: In large Teflon coated frypan, heat olive oil over medium heat.
Cook chourico sausage, onion and garlic until sausage is cooked through and vegetables are softened and begin to brown. Remove chourico and set aside.

title: ginger tea
directions: Mix molasses with ginger.
Pour on the boiling water slowly and boil for one minute.
Add hot milk and serve.

title: peach - jello pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add water.
Stir well.
Put in microwave and cook on High for 6 to 8 minutes.
Stir in Jell-O. Let cool.
Add peaches and sugar if they are bitter.
Pour in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: company salisbury steak
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients; form into patties.
Fry 7 to 8 minutes in hot oil or butter.
Garnish with hot sauteed mushrooms.

title: buttermilk puffs
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, nutmeg and salt.
With a fork, stir in buttermilk, cooking oil and egg. Beat until smooth.
Drop by teaspoons into hot fat at 375°.
Too large puffs will not cook through.
Drain on paper towels.
Roll warm rolls in 4x sugar that has been sifted.

title: szechwan shrimp
directions: Dissolve together the cornstarch and sherry, then add chicken broth, soy sauce, ketchup, chili paste and sugar.

Set aside. Preheat a pan until hot then add the oil. Add garlic, ginger and shrimp, stir fry for 2 minutes, shrimp will be pink and becoming firm. Add the scallions and stir fry for 1 more minute. Add the broth mixture and stir until thickened. Serve with rice. Peapods may be added with the onions.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In baking pan, blend all ingredients except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to coat thoroughly.
Bake, stirring potatoes occasionally, 60 minutes or until tender and golden brown.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Mix Love and Loyalty constantly with Faith.
Blend in Tenderness, Kindness and Understanding.
Add Friendship for flavor and Hope for success.
Sprinkle abundantly with Laughter.
Bake during family worship and serve generous helpings daily.

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time. Add salt
and stir in chocolate syrup, flour and vanilla.
Add nuts
and
blend well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 8-inch square
microwave
pan
or
dish.
Cook on High power for about 3 minutes, let set for 3 minutes, then on High power	again for 3 minutes, let set 3 times.
Last, microwave on
High
for
2 minutes or until batter sets to your liking. Cut
into
squares and remove from pan.
Garnish with nuts and powdered
sugar. Shield
corner of dish with foil triangle to cook
evenly.	Turn dish
half	turn
after each 3 minutes of cooking unless microwave is rotating one.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch.
Cook until thick and clear. Add strawberries.
Pour into a 9-inch baked pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: sugar buns
directions: Place sugar, salt and butter in a bowl.
Mix smoothly and pour the scalded milk over them.
Let this cool to lukewarm, then add the well-beaten eggs and dissolved yeast.
Add half of the flour and beat well.
Stir in remaining flour adding more, if needed. (Dough should form a soft ball on the spoon and come away from the side of the bowl.)
Set bowl in a warm place, free from drafts, until dough doubles in bulk.
Stir well and let raise again until double in bulk.
Stir well and let raise again until double in bulk.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead several times.
Roll to about 1/4-inch thickness.
Brush with melted butter.
Sprinkle thickly with sugar and cinnamon (nuts or raisins are optional). Roll (jelly-roll fashion) and slice in pieces 1-inch long.
Place in a well-greased pan and allow to rise until double in size.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fall caramel abby applesauce
directions: Pare, core and cut apples into small wedges.
Melt margarine. Add brown sugar in saucepan over low heat.
Remove saucepan from heat.
Stir in apples; coat with brown sugar and margarine mixture.
Add water and nutmeg.
Cook apples over medium-high heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer on low for about 20 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Dot with butter.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: caramel layer squares
directions: Blend in double boiler or microwave the caramels and evaporated milk.
Mix together until dough holds together the cake mix, melted oleo and evaporated milk.

title: rum cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except sugar, in large bowl.
Stir and blend.
Using 1 teaspoon at a time, form into a ball. Roll in sugar.
Store in covered jar.
I store them in the fridge.

title: homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown meat in deep steak pot.
Add water to cover and plus. Add celery and onion.
Add tomatoes, carrots and potatoes during the last hour of cooking.
Season to taste and add spaghetti the last 30 minutes.
Other vegetables may be added.
Do not add potatoes if you plan to freeze.

title: elegant frosting
directions: Combine sugar and milk in heavy saucepan; bring to boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat and simmer 6 minutes without stirring. Remove from heat; add chocolate. Stir to blend. Stir in butter and vanilla. Chill until mixture begins to thicken. Beat until thick and frost.

title: baked beans
directions: Cut up bacon and cook with sliced onions and garlic about 10 minutes.
Combine all ingredients and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: cottage cheese dessert
directions: Mix dry Jell-O into cottage cheese.
Add mandarin oranges and pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Serve with hollowed out pumpernickel round bread. Dip with bread sticks.

title: pantry chicken casserole
directions: Separate crescent dough into 8 rectangles.
Press at perforations to seal.
Roll out each rectangle and cut in halves, forming 16 squares.
Combine chicken and 1 cup cheese; put 2 tablespoons mixture in each square of dough.
Roll up, allowing edges to overlap.
Put in shallow casserole, seam down.
Combine milk, soup and 1 cup cheese.
Spread over chicken roll-ups and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until dough is cooked and casserole bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry-jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O.
Add 2 small packages frozen strawberries (undrained).
Mash 3 bananas and add to drained crushed pineapple. Add nuts (optional).
Pour half mixture in pan.
Let jell. Spread with sour cream, then pour remaining Jell-O into pan and jell.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine butter and peanut butter in a 2-quart glass bowl. Cover with paper towel and microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High power.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Press mixture into an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch dish.
Combine chocolate chips and shortening in a 2 cup glass bowl and microwave at Medium power 2 minutes or until chocolate melts.
Spread over peanut butter mixture.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: stuffed manicotti shells
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to directions; drain.
Mix onion, spinach, bouillon, garlic powder, thyme, cottage cheese, eggs and Parmesan.
Fill shells with mixture; arrange in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour tomato sauce over shells.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
Cover and cook at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 25 minutes.
Makes five servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Can be frozen on trays and sealed for later.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix molasses and baking powder; add to batter.
Mix spices to flour; alternate flour and liquid.
Add raisins, currants and walnuts.
Pour in greased and floured tube pans.
Bake in a 250° oven for 3 hours.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Layer ingredients; repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown meat; drain off any fat.
Add onion and green pepper. Add other ingredients and simmer for about 30 minutes. Serve on buns.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together ingredients, adding all but 1/2 the cheese.
Heat oil and pour mixture in skillet while hot.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Great!

title: pralines
directions: Boil sugars and water until soft ball stage (240°).
Remove and add dash of salt, vanilla and butter.
Beat until gloss comes off and spoon immediately onto wax paper.

title: bee sting cake
directions: Mix butter, cake mix and 1 egg and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream powdered sugar and cream cheese; add 2 eggs.
Mix well and pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Options: Chocolate or butter cake mixes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrots and bacon
directions: Wash and trim carrots; split into 2-inch lengths.
Wrap each carrot with 1 bacon half and secure with toothpick.
Wrap in tinfoil loosely and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until carrots and bacon are done.
Do not add water.

title: moxie berry pie
directions: Mix together Jell-O, salt, cornstarch, sugar and water.
Cook 5 minutes after bubbling.
Put berries in pie shell.
Pour sauce over berries.
Refrigerate a few hours.
Top with whipped cream.

title: seafood horseradish sauce
directions: Add horseradish to mayonnaise and mix well.
Add more horseradish if not spicy enough.
Good substitute for tartar sauce.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into boiling chicken broth.
Cover; simmer 5 to 8 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place in order as listed preceeding peas; spread 1 to 2 cups Hellmann's mayonnaise (regular or light) with 1 tablespoon sugar per cup (mixed in).
Cover well with any kind of grated sharp cheese.
Cover with bacon bits.
Let set 24 hours (or less), your choice.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Blend together soups, cream, lobster and cayenne and bring to simmering point.
When mixture is hot, stir in sherry and butter. Serve with sprinkling of chives and Parmesan cheese croutons.

title: "sea legs" crabmeat casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except stuffing mix; mix lightly. Pour into prepared casserole; sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, stir together the strawberries, eggs, oil and sugar until combined.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add them to the batter, stirring just to blend.
Fold in the chopped nuts.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool on a rack for 15 minutes before removing from the pan.

title: old fashioned gold cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add well beaten egg yolks and sugar; beat well.
Sift flour, soda and cornstarch 3 times.
Add alternately the flour and sour milk.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until firm to the touch, in moderate 375° oven.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat your oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes. Check doneness with toothpick.

title: cornflake kisses
directions: Melt chocolate.
Mix with cornflakes.
Drop on waxed paper by spoonfuls and let harden.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on platter, spread 1/2 to 3/4 seafood sauce on cheese.
Drain shrimp and layer on top of sauce. Refrigerate until cold.
Serve with crackers.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Good served on rye bread or crackers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all ingredients; pour in pan and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: individual barbecue pizzas
directions: Brown hamburger, salt and pepper to taste; drain grease. Place a biscuit in the bottom of each muffin holder.
Mix barbecue sauce with hamburger.
Spoon hamburger mixture onto biscuits. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are done.

title: creole squash
directions: Lightly brown bacon.
Add onion and cook until golden brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer until tender (15 to 20 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: swiss potatoes
directions: Sprinkle potatoes with salt and pepper.
Cream the butter or bacon drippings until very soft.
Beat the egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Blend with sour cream and butter or bacon drippings.
Mix with potatoes and fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 10-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle generously with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Oil 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put all ingredients into pan and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake the following day for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350° in a covered pan (uncover the final 15 minutes of baking time).
Serves 10.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 greased skillets. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and applesauce; add beaten eggs. Add cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda, flour, raisins (dusted with flour) and walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients in 1 tablespoon Crisco oil.
Pour off oil.
Add the pork and beans.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into large baking dish.

title: peas with prosciutto
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan and saute onion gently, 5 to 6 minutes.
Add stock and peas.
Bring to boil; cover.
Simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add Prosciutto.
Cook, uncovered, stirring frequently, until liquid is absorbed.
Serve hot.

title: spice tea
directions: Combine.
Mix with water to desired taste.
Heat and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions and oleo.
Add broccoli and soup.
Cook until tender.
Add other ingredients, saving bread crumbs to sprinkle on top.
Pour in casserole and cook.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until bread crumbs brown.

title: steph's appetizer
directions: Slice all the ingredients, then put in on platter.

title: peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Put the 2 slices of bread on the plate.
Spread the peanut butter on both slices of bread.
Then spread the jelly on top of the peanut butter.
Then you put the two pieces of bread together.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Bring sugar, butter and milk to a boil and cook 3 minutes. Remove from heat and add chocolate morsels.
Cool and beat smooth.

title: easy pumpkin swirl
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; line with wax paper and grease wax paper.
Set aside.
Beat eggs at high speed with mixer until thickened.
Gradually add sugar, beating until soft peak forms and sugar dissolves (2 to 4 minutes).
Fold in pumpkin.
Combine biscuit mix and spices; fold into pumpkin mixture and spread evenly into prepared pan. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Heat first 2 ingredients over low heat.
Remove from heat and mix in other ingredients in order.
Place mixture in a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Microwave on High for all steps.

title: aunt davies cranberry salad
directions: Grind the cranberries in blender. Add 2 cups sugar and set aside.
Mix the gelatin as directed on package. Refrigerate until thickened.
Mix all ingredients together with thickened gelatin and cranberries.
Refrigerate.
Makes about 1 gallon.

title: inside out cake
directions: Combine all ingredients (except chocolate chips) in bowl and mix for 2 minutes.
Fold in chips.
Pour in lightly greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
(Don't overbake.
Cake is done when springs back.)
Cool for 15 minutes before tipping out onto serving dish.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: bobbie's banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions less 1/2 cup milk, add half of the Kool Whip and the Eagle Brand milk; add vanilla.
Layer in dish:
vanilla wafers, pudding, bananas and cover with the rest of the Kool Whip.

title: pineapple carrot cookies
directions: Drain pineapple (well).
Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in pineapple, carrots, nuts and raisins. Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat into pineapple mixture until well blended.
Drop by heaping tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten tops with spoon.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: corn and chive souffle
directions: Butter tall 2-quart souffle dish. Blend together corn, cheese and egg yolks. Add chives and season to taste. Beat egg whites to soft peaks, adding cream of tartar, when they become foamy. Stir a quarter of whites into corn mixture to lighten it. Fold in remaining whites. Pour into souffle dish and bake at 425° oven for 10 minutes. Turn heat to 375° and cook for 30 minutes more. Serve immediately.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and slice potatoes thinly.
Set aside in a bowl of cold water.
Melt butter in a saucepan or frying pan. Add flour and stir constantly until bubbly.
Gradually stir in milk and continue to stir until mixture thickens.
Add salt (more if desired).
Remove from heat.

title: bishop's stew beef
directions: Salt and pepper beef; coat in flour.
Brown stew beef in oil. Put meat in a 9 x 13-inch dish sprayed with Pam.
Saute onions and peppers in butter.
Layer onions, peppers and mushrooms over beef. Combine remaining ingredients into a sauce.
Mix well; pour over beef.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Check to see if it needs more water at 1 to 2 hours.

title: patsy's vegetable dip
directions: Mix, chill and serve.

title: black bean and corn ranch salsa
directions: In a medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Chill. Serve with tostado or corn chips.

title: spinach squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish in oven. Remove dish. Beat eggs well, then add flour, milk, salt and baking powder. Mix well. Add cheese, spinach and onion and mix well. Spoon into dish and level off. Sprinkle with seasoned salt, if desired. Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Cool and cut into squares.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Place in bowl and beat at high speed until smooth.
Line muffin tins or use aluminum foil cups on cookie sheet.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in each cup.
Fill each cup about 3/4 with cheese mixture. Let cool.
Top with your favorite Musselman's pie fillings (cherry, blueberry, apple).
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chicken with muenster cheese
directions: Slightly flatten chicken breasts.
Dredge in seasoned flour, shaking off excess.
In medium skillet, heat 1/4 cup butter with oil.
Saute chicken until lightly brown and cooked through (about 4 minutes on each side).
Transfer chicken to an oven dish; add wine and bring to a boil, stirring in the brown bits.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Heat butter; saute mushrooms for 5 minutes.
Preheat broiler.
Top chicken with slices of cheese. Pour mushrooms over chicken.
Place under broiler for 3 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs until stiff.
Add sugar, one cup at a time.
Mix flour with baking powder.
Melt milk and butter together.
Add these.
Bake in 2 layer pans at 325°.

title: taco salad
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in dry taco seasoning mix and water; simmer 10 minutes over low heat. Line separate salad bowls or plates with lettuce; sprinkle with corn chips.
Spoon about 1/2 cup beef mixture in center; sprinkle with cheese.
Garnish with tomatoes.
Serve immediately with combination of chili sauce and Tabasco sauce.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Parboil seafood, reserving stock.
Make roux by browning flour in oil.
Add onion and garlic, stirring frequently until slightly wilted.
Add tomatoes, sauce, seafood stock and seasonings.
Stir well; simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add okra and additional stock or water, if necessary.
Bring to boil.
Add seafood; simmer another 10 minutes.
Serve over hot rice.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Mix the rhubarb, flour, sugar and water; let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Cook the next morning and add the jello and pineapple.

title: gennetts
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla in blender.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually add egg mixture to form dough.
Add additional flour as needed to make a soft ball of dough.
Let rest on floured counter top for 1/2 to 1 hour.
To form cookies, pull off small amounts of dough to form 1-inch balls. Roll ball in hands to form a roll approximately 3 x 1/4 to 1/2-inch.
Wrap roll around your finger to shape a small "beehive" form and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown, approximately 5 to 8 minutes.
Watch closely to prevent scorching.
Let cool completely.

title: meringue
directions: Combine water, sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan, stirring well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until transparent and thickened.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Continue beating while gradually pouring cooked mixture into egg whites.
Beat for 3 minutes, or until stiff, but not dry, peaks form.
Makes enough for one pie.

title: herb parmesan bread
directions: Brush frozen loaf with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Cover.
Thaw at room temperature for 2 to 3 hours or in refrigerator 6 to 10 hours.
Sprinkle loaf with 1/3 cup cheese.
Knead until well blended.
Cut dough into thirds.
On lightly floured surface, roll each third into a 25-inch rope.
Braid ropes together.
Invert a 10 ounce custard cup on a greased baking sheet, grease cup.
Shape braid into wreath around cup.
Pinch ends together to seal.
Brush with remaining margarine.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and basil.
Let rise 35 to 45 minutes until doubled.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until golden and done. Remove to rack and cool.

title: pound cake with caramel icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar, mix in 1 egg at a time. Add milk, then flour, vanilla and almond flavorings. Stir well. Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: toffee bars
directions: Separate graham crackers and place side by side on a greased jelly roll pan so that they are close but not touching. Melt margarine and butter together. Add sugar and boil until slightly thickened. Spoon butter mixture over each individual cracker. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and bake at 350° for 8-10 minutes. Transfer immediately to wax paper or parchment paper. Cool. Dip top side with nuts into melted chocolate. Cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of oleo. Put the bread in a medium size bowl and pour over the melted oleo; toss well and set aside.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onion; cover with pickling salt.
Let stand for 2 hours; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients together and boil.
Add cucumbers and onions and cook until they turn color.

title: fruit salad(diabetic)
directions: If using fresh fruit with canned fruit, drain canned fruit and combine the two before mixing the pudding.
Mix buttermilk and pudding together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place 1/2 of fruit in bowl. Top with pudding mixture and remaining fruit on top.
Makes 10 servings/169 calories per serving.

title: coconut cream icebox pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; gradually add milk, stirring until smooth. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly and boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir half of hot mixture into egg yolks. Add remaining hot mixture and stir over low heat until it boils and is thick, about 5 minutes. Turn into a bowl and stir in extracts and half of coconut. Cover with wax paper and refrigerate 1 hour. Place in baked pie shell and refrigerate 3 hours. Spread Cool Whip over filling and top with remaining coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: savory stuffed peppers
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Stir in corn, tomato sauce and steak sauce.
Remove tops, core and seeds from peppers.
Spoon mixture into peppers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in thin strips.
Place in dish.
Add soy sauce. Slice the peppers and onions into small strips; lay on top of steak.
Let this set overnight or all day.
Keep cool.
Fry the steak on low until browned.
Add the peppers, onions and soy sauce and let simmer for about 20 minutes or until veggies are soft.

title: strawberry pie filling
directions: Combine jello, cornstarch and sugar.
Add cold water and mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens slightly and becomes clear.
Add a few drops of red food coloring.
Cool until lukewarm.

title: savory potato gratin(4 servings)
directions: Saute onions in butter in a large skillet until soft and transparent.
In a shallow baking dish, arrange in layers the sliced onions and potatoes, sprinkling with garlic and seasonings in between layers for best flavor.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Add whipping cream all over top.
Increase temperature to 400°.
Bake for another 10 to 20 minutes until potatoes are soft and fork-tender and gratin is slightly browned on top.

title: crepes
directions: Mix all ingredients together; use 1/2 cup for measure.
Fry in butter until brown on both sides.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease baking sheet.
Sift into mixing bowl the flour, baking powder, cream of tartar, sugar and salt with pastry blender.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Beat egg lightly and add to milk.
Add liquid to dry ingredients and blend until dough holds together.
Turn dough onto a floured board and knead lightly.
Roll 1-inch thick and cut into biscuits.
Bake 12 minutes.
Makes about 24.

title: wiener-kraut bake(low calorie - 210 calories)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sauerkraut, vegetable juice, onion and mustard and place in casserole.
Place frankfurters on top of sauerkraut mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top with green pepper rings and bake another 10 minutes. Serves 4.

title: scotch treats
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter over hot water.
Stir to blend. Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Stir until well coated.

title: grandma's sauerbraten
directions: Marinate meat at least 2 days in water, vinegar, onions, pickling spice, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer meat in marinade 3 to 4 hours until tender (i.e. cook like pot roast after browning meat).
Turn occasionally.
Strain gravy.
Brown flour in a pan, then add to gravy mix.
Put in gingersnaps and meat to thicken gravy.

title: spice drop cookies
directions: Mix zucchini, baking soda, sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Mix well.
Then add nuts and raisins.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Mix drained beans, peas, pimento, celery and onion.
Make a dressing of the sugar, vinegar, oil and seasonings in pan; heat to boiling.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.
Drain well before serving.
Keeps several days. Yields 12 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: In a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole, layer lettuce, celery, peppers, eggs, onion, peas and bacon.
Mix salad dressing with sugar.
Spread on top
of layers.
Seal edges.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: 7 (plus) layer dip
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain thoroughly.
Add taco seasoning according to directions.
In large clear glass casserole, layer meat mixture, then refried beans.
Let cool.

title: cornstarch goop
directions: Put a few spoonfuls of cornstarch into a cup.
Add water, a few drops at a time, until the cornstarch is pasty.
Now pick up this goop and squeeze it, it's crumbly.
Hold it loosely, it oozes through your fingers.
It's as though you can change the substance from a liquid to a solid by simply squeezing it.

title: four-layer dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Blend together flour, margarine or butter and pecans.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; don't salt.
Bone and break into pieces.
Melt the oleo; stir in the stuffing mix.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer the stuffing mix and chicken soup mix with broth until all has been used.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Mix with a little oleo.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter.
Mix pecans and coconut in butter and brown lightly.
Set aside.
Blend together milk and cheese until smooth. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put 1/4 of Cool Whip mixture in bottom of each crust pan.
Drizzle 3 ounces of caramel sauce on top.
Sprinkle some of the coconut mixture on top.
Repeat layers.
Freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.

title: honey whole wheat bread
directions: Combine in mixer bowl: 3 cups whole wheat flour, nonfat dry milk, salt and dry yeast packages.
Heat in saucepan until warm: water, honey and oil.
Pour warm (not hot) liquid over flour mixture.
Beat with electric mixer for 3 minutes.
Stir in: 1 cup whole wheat flour and white flour.
Knead 5 minutes, using additional white flour, if necessary.
Place in greased bowl, turn and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down, divide dough in half and shape into loaves.
Place in greased 9 x 5-inch bread pans.
Cover and let rise 40 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix 3/4 cup of stuffing mix with melted butter.
Mix egg, corn, grated onion, salt and pepper.
Add drained broccoli.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Sprinkle 1/4 cup crumbs over and bake at 350° until done.

title: tuna carrot salad
directions: Combine tuna, carrots, celery and onion in bowl; set aside. Mix together mayonnaise, milk and mustard; toss gently.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Add shoestring potatoes and toss. Makes 6 servings.

title: wild rice and turkey casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed.
Brown sausage and drain.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix ingredients and put in dish.
Bake 30 minutes, covered, at 350°.

title: heavenly green pea soup
directions: Put all ingredients into large soup pot.
Let boil for 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes stirring often.
When peas are mushy, add salt and pepper to taste and water if too thick.
Soup may be frozen for future use.
Remove garlic pod "if you can find it."
"Bon appetite."

title: penne and chicken di genoa
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In large skillet over medium heat, cook chicken in oil until brown. Add pasta sauce; heat.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all together and bake in 2 bread pans at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add nuts and apples.
Stir well and spread in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bake one pie shell until brown.
Heat drained Veg-All with a little butter, salt and pepper until hot.
Add soup and chicken. Pour into one browned pie shell.
Place other crust on top.
Seal edges and bake at 325° to 350° until brown.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: In a bowl, combine the eggs, water, milk and oil.
Stir in mixes and mix well.
Fill greased and floured muffin cups half full.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until muffins test done.
Cool for 5 minutes; remove from pans to wire racks.
Yield: 14 muffins.

title: tuna pate
directions: Place tuna, cognac, pepper and dill weed in blender and blend until
smooth.
Add
cream cheese and eggs.
Whip until smooth. Fold
in
pistachios and place in small serving bowl. Chill. Serve with crackers. Makes about 2 cups.

title: bread machine honey wheat bread
directions: Follow instructions on bread machine.
May be used on rapid, regular or delayed cycles.

title: pork chops and vegetables
directions: Place pork chops in a skillet and brown on both sides. Enough fat should cook out of the chops so that is not necessary to add any to the skillet. Remove chops from skillet. Place onions and green pepper in skillet and cook until tender, add fat if needed. Add mushroom soup, water, rice, peas, salt and pepper. Mix well. Pour half the rice mixture into a greased baking dish, arrange half the pork chops over rice and peas. Top with remaining chops and rice. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: kim chee(pickled cabbage)
directions: Soak cabbage overnight in 1 quart of water with 1/4 cup of salt.
Next morning drain all but 1/2 cup of water.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Press tightly into quart jars and cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 4 days.
Refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: autumn soup
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add onion and brown slightly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boil.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Blend in lard.
Add beaten egg and lemon juice.
Add enough water to make dough.
Roll between wax paper.
Cut dough into squares big enough to cover an apple.

title: melanie's party brie
directions: Cook brown sugar and brandy over medium heat.
