Stir and let thicken and turn to a heavy sauce.
Pour over the Brie and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Decorate top with walnuts and serve with small dinner rolls or crackers of your choice.

title: buckeyes
directions: In large bowl, add butter, peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Mix until creamy.
Roll into balls about the size of walnuts (makes quite a few).
Place on wax paper; refrigerate. While refrigerating, melt candy in double boiler.
Add Gulfwax. When all melted, add balls with toothpick.
Poke balls; dip in chocolate, leaving an oval eye on top.
Put back on wax paper and refrigerate.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix crushed crackers, oleo and sugar together. Reserving 1/2 cup to garnish, put in bottom of 9 x 12-inch dish or pan. Mix undiluted orange juice in
Eagle Brand milk. Add thawed Cool Whip and gently fold in mandarin oranges. Pour this mixture over cracker mixture.
Sprinkle garnish over salad and refrigerate.

title: banana surprise cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and then add rest of ingredients.
Put nuts and raisins last.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: circus peanuts (candy) salad
directions: Cut peanuts into small pieces and add 1 cup cold water. Sprinkle dry Jell-O into peanuts and water.
Cook until peanuts melt.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and chill until thick (freeze).
Add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle crushed nuts on top.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti by directions on box, adding a little butter to keep it from sticking.
Let cool.
Chop the vegetables and add to spaghetti.
Then stir in the dressing and salad seasoning. Refrigerate.
This will keep several days.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order given, using as much or as little as you prefer.
Cover entire surface of salad with mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar.
Add some shredded Cheddar cheese to the top.
Cover container and refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Stir every hour after putting in freezer.
Set out at room temperature.
Allow 5 hours thaw time.

title: annette's lemon bars
directions: Cream the butter and powdered sugar until light color. Gradually add flour, blending well.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan so it goes up sides, so filling does not get on sides.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until crust begins to brown.

title: super simple brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir until blended. Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan for about 25 minutes at 350°. Allow to cool completely before cutting.

title: karol's dip
directions: Mix well.
Good for raw vegetables or chips.

title: peppy popcorn mix
directions: Mix popcorn, pretzels and crackers.
Divide evenly into 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine	in
casserole
and
mix with the next 3 ingredients.
Pat over
bottom of dish and bake at 350° for 12 to 15	minutes.
Cool	completely.
Mix
powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip; spread on crust and put in refrigerator.
Mix pudding
according
to
instructions on package, using the
milk and
spread.
Spread
balance of container of Cool Whip
over pudding mix. Sprinkle with chopped pecans and chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: nachos grande
directions: Brown ground beef (flavor with garlic powder and onion powder); drain.
Deep-fry tortilla chips for 30 seconds; drain. Finely chop onion.
Cover cookie sheet with foil, then layer chips, ground beef, onion and cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes to melt cheese.
Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: low-fat pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Divide evenly into 2 pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake another 45 minutes or until knife inserted into each pie comes out clean.
Cool before serving.

title: apple rolls
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening as for pie crust.
Add milk and mix.
Roll out about 1/4-inch thick on floured surface.
Spread apples over dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar.
Roll up as for jelly roll.
Cut into 12 slices and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil 1 1/2 cups sugar and 2 cups water.
Pour over rolls.
Bake at 375° until brown. Serve with whipped cream.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces. Season with salt and pepper.
Place in crock-pot with sliced onion.
Pour tomatoes over all.
Cook on low 8 to 10 hours.

title: mint tea
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour boiling water over tea mixture, cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Remove tea bags and mint sprigs; discard.
Transfer tea to a large pitcher and add water, pineapple juice and lemonade concentrate; stir well.
Serve over ice and garnish with mint sprigs.
Yield: 2 1/2 quarts.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Spread meat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer on onion, cheese and Doritos.
Mix tomatoes, soups and broth.
Pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: quick peanut butter bars
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden.

title: pistachio mousse
directions: Let Cool Whip topping sit out at room temperature for about 1 hour.
In a large bowl, fold in pudding (uncooked), crushed pineapple with juice and mandarin oranges with half juice. Reserve 5 slices for garnish.
Once all ingredients are folded in, blend in slowly the Cool Whip topping. Do not whip or beat or it will become watery.

title: mom's dinner meat loaf
directions: Brown and drain ground meat.
Lightly saute onion and bell pepper.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients and, using your hands, mix everything together well.
Spray cooking spray on 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Put meat mixture into baking dish and pack well.
Bake in 350° oven for about an hour.
Drain off any excess grease that cooks out of the meat loaf.
Cover top of meat loaf with ketchup and cook for 15 more minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Arrange cookie slices on pan in a circular pattern, slightly overlapping.
Press lightly together to seal.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Do not whip Dream Whip; use right from envelope.
Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Combine brown sugar and butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange pineapple slices in pan, cutting slices if necessary.
Place a cherry half, cut side up, in center of each slice.
Sprinkle with reserved juice and the nuts. Combine cake mix, whipped topping mix right from envelope, eggs and water in
large mixer bowl.
Blend, then beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Carefully spoon over mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until top springs back when lightly pressed.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes, then invert onto serving plate.
Let stand 1 minute, then remove pan. Serve warm or cold.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mash all ingredients together.	Put in Pyrex dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tea bars
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and butter.
Add to mixture pecans, coconut and chocolate chips.
Turn the mixture into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until center is set. Wonderful!!

title: busy day meal for one
directions: Fold tinfoil over patty and vegetables, being sure all edges are sealed securely to prevent escape of steam.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in the oven about 1 hour at 350°.

title: granny bell's mexican corn bread
directions: Crush jalapeno pepper in cornmeal.
Mix all other ingredients except cheese.
Heat and grease skillet.
Pour in 1/2 of cornmeal mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 of cheese and pour in rest of cornmeal mixture.
Sprinkle the rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Have skillet very hot when you pour in cornmeal mixture to prevent sticking.

title: baked fish fillets
directions: Cut fillets into 4 portions and soak 3 minutes in milk to which salt has been added.
Drain and roll in bread crumbs, place fish in greased baking dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 450° allowing 8 minutes if fish is fresh and 15 minutes if fish is frozen.
Yield:
4 servings.
Carbohydrate 5 g, protein 22 g, fat 13 g, calories 225.
One serving = 3 meat low-fat exchange.

title: marci's sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook yams and sweet potatoes until tender when poked with fork; drain.
Partially cool and peel, removing any discolored portions.
Mash; add softened margarine and brown sugar while still warm.
Place in bowl, using electric mixer or blender until nice and smooth.
Grease large casserole dish.
Place half mixture in dish, placing part of marshmallows on top.
Add remainder of mixture and smooth top.
Place in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until nice and hot.
Poke remaining marshmallows uniformly on top. Return to oven just until marshmallows are lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: mustard sauce and dip
directions: Melt margarine in small saucepan; remove from heat.
Add cornstarch and turmeric; mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Makes about 1 cup.
Use as a basting sauce for baked, broiled or microwaved seafood.
Serve as a sauce or dip for fish, turkey, ham or chicken nuggets or poached meats or fish.

title: pear honey
directions: Mix well and cook until the juice becomes thick. Put in jars and seal.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook over low heat, stirring often.
Do not boil, but allow cheese to melt.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Add crumbled Blue cheese and let sit refrigerated overnight before serving. Keeps well for 3 weeks.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop and mix vegetables and sprinkle sugar over them.
In saucepan, combine vinegar, celery seed, salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil; add oil and bring to a boil again.
Pour over vegetables. Cool and refrigerate.
Will keep 2 weeks.

title: cobbler pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add baking powder and salt, then add milk slowly.
Melt butter in baking dish and add the batter.
Put fruit on top of batter in small pieces and add juice.
Bake at 325° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes hawaiian
directions: Cook potatoes in water in skins until tender.
Remove skins and cream.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain pineapple.
In large bowl combine sweet potatoes, pineapple, 1/2 cup butter, granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Beat until well blended and creamy.
Put in casserole dish; sprinkle with brown sugar and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° and serve immediately.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar.
In separate bowl mix crushed pineapple, strawberries, chopped nuts, bananas and Cool Whip. Combine with cream cheese mixture.
Spoon into loaf pan.
Freeze. Cut into slices.
Serve frozen.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Thaw lemonade.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add milk.
Fold in whipping cream topping until smooth.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Chill and serve.

title: frozen raspberry pie
directions: Thaw and drain raspberries.
Reserve a few for garnish. Combine raspberries, sugar, egg whites, lemon juice and salt. Beat for 15 minutes or until stiff.
Fold in whipped cream and almonds.
Mound in baked pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with reserved raspberries.

title: pea casserole
directions: Drain peas; pour in casserole dish.
Mix soup with peas.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Take out; sprinkle fried onion rings on top. Put back in oven until onion rings are brown.

title: crab dip
directions: Dissolve gelatine in cold water in a small bowl. Heat soup, but do not add water or milk. Let cool 10 minutes.

Mix into dissolved gelatine. Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl. Mix well. Add the soup mixture to other ingredients in large bowl. Pour into jello mold and let set 3 to 4 hours or overnight before serving.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl until mixture is smooth. Pour into greased pie pans. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: green chili burros
directions: Spread the refried beans on the tortillas.
Then, divide the ground meat and top with cheese.
Roll up and put in baking dish. Cover with a can of green chili enchilada sauce.
(I like Hatch's brand.)
Cover the top with grated cheese and heat until the cheese is melted and the sauce is bubbly, about 15 to 20 minutes at 350° (or microwave).

title: apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 3 (1 pound) coffee cans.
Blend sugar and eggs.
Add oil, sour cream, vanilla
and apples.
Combine dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Pour into coffee cans. Bake, upright, at 350° for 1 hour. Shake out onto wire rack to cool, then return to coffee cans.
Apply lids and store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix sugar, egg and butter until creamy; add sour milk and soda and stir well.
Add flour, cocoa and baking powder; mix well.
Add boiling water and vanilla.
Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or test with toothpick.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Cook chicken with enough water to cover until tender.
Take off heat.
Fix stuffing, using 2 cups chicken broth and eliminating butter.
Spread stuffing in 13 x 9-inch pan. Put chicken over stuffing.
Cook broccoli and place over chicken.
Mix soup and milk.
Mix cheese.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken with prunes and honey
directions: Truss the chickens; put in a thick bottomed saucepan with the offal, salt, pepper, saffron,
the stick of cinnamon, grated onions and butter.
Add 2 big glassfuls of water.
Cook with the lid on, over a moderate heat, turning the chickens from time to time.
Add water if necessary.
When the chickens are cooked and the flesh comes off the bones in the fingers easily, take off the heat and put on one side.
Wash the prunes and put in the saucepan still on the heat.
Fifteen minutes later, add the honey and cinnamon.
Boil the sauce down until it is syrupy.
Check the seasoning and put the chickens back in the saucepan without crushing the prunes.
Remove from the heat.

title: holiday bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, break bread into small pieces. Add raisins, milk, pineapple, cherries and coconut.
Mix well.
In a large mixing bowl, cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and food coloring.
Mix well. Add margarine mixture to bread mixture.
Pour into a 3-quart pan.
Bake for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
Serves 10. Contains 200 calories per serving.

title: best brownies
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine; add cocoa and sugar.
Add egg yolks, flour, vanilla and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salt water until tender.
Drain. Saute carrots and onions in 4 teaspoons of butter until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups bread cubes, soup and sour cream.
Stir in zucchini.
Turn into casserole; melt remaining butter.
Add remaining bread cubes to butter.
Toss; top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken tater topper
directions: Saute the onion and mushrooms in the oil in a large skillet. Stir in water and flour.
Gradually add the milk until thickened. Add the seasonings, chicken and broccoli; cook, uncovered, for 2 to 3 minutes.
Slice open potatoes and pour broccoli mixture on top. Makes 4 servings.
Contains 9 grams of fat per serving.

title: punch
directions: Mix together in order as written.
Chill and serve.

title: banana oatmeal muffins
directions: In a medium bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add the banana, egg and butter or margarine to the oatmeal mixture.
Add dry ingredients to the banana mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: oyster stew
directions: *May substitute 1/2 pound diced ham for oysters

title: holiday fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit together.
Pour peach pie filling over fruit and mix well.
Chill before serving.

title: strawberry cream cheese dessert(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, sour cream, vanilla and Cool Whip together. Break cake into small pieces. Layer into large glass bowl. Layer pudding, cake and strawberries. Start over again for second layer. End with pudding mixture and garnish with strawberries. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheese enchilada(mexican food)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and toss together lightly. A chilled tortilla has a tendency to crack when rolled, so heat 1 can of the enchilada sauce and dip each of the thawed tortillas into the warm sauce.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons of the cheese mixture in the center of the tortilla and roll.
Place, seam side down, in a greased baking dish. Cover with remaining can of enchilada sauce and bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place 2 cups of rhubarb in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a mixing bowl, combine butter, 1 cup of sugar, flour, milk and baking powder; mix well and pour over rhubarb.
Mix hot water and 1 1/2 cups of sugar together and stir until dissolved.
Place remaining rhubarb on top of batter and pour the sugar-water mixture over all.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: paul hartel pastry crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, not too fine, then add water. Squeeze together with hands and roll out to about 1/4-inch thick. Chill well before cooking and bake at 450° for 10 minutes for tarts, then reduce heat to 350°.

title: herman cinnamon rolls
directions: Spread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place slices of dough, flat side down, on top and bake in a 350° oven about 1/2 hour, until golden brown.
Invert onto plate.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar, creaming well.
Add vanilla, eggs and bananas.
Mix dry ingredients; fold into banana mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian roasted potatoes
directions: Peel, wash and dry potatoes thoroughly and cut into quarters. Dry potatoes again after cutting.
Melt margarine and shortening together in pan.
Mix pepper, rosemary and garlic and sprinkle over potatoes.
Baste potatoes with margarine and shortening and mix well.
Place 2 tablespoons shortening on flat baking pan and allow to melt in oven evenly.
Take out the hot pan and place cold potatoes, spaced apart, onto the pan.
Place pan in 350° oven and bake 60 to 90 minutes or when potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: economy loaf
directions: Call your local Pizza Hut.
Place order and wait for delivery.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cheese, Accent, 1 package dried beef and onion.
Then roll in 1 package dried beef.
Cut up dried beef in small pieces.

title: corn custard(corn pudding)
directions: Combine eggs, salt, pepper, sugar, corn, butter and milk. Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set in pan of hot water (1-inch deep).
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until silver knife inserted near center comes out clean. Serves 6.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Put in pan brown sugar and mustard.
Mix together in blender onion and hot peppers.
Cook over medium heat for 20 minutes.
Add flour and juice from onion and peppers.

title: quick fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine meat and package of Lipton soup.
Mix well.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan, pressing out evenly.
Next, layer green beans, followed by 1/2 can soup of choice.
Top with a layer of croutons, covered with remaining 1/2 can of soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Then uncover and finish baking, usually 1/2 hour.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery soup

title: deer chili
directions: Brown both meats, then drain.
Add onion and chili powder to meat.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours before eating (3 to 4 hours in a crock-pot on medium heat works well, too!).

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients with a small amount of milk.
Add remaining milk.
Cook over boiling water, stirring until thick. Cover and cook for 15 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Add a small amount of hot mixture to egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture and cook a few minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla; stir well. Slice bananas into pie shell.
Pour filling over.
Cool slightly.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Have cooked rice ready; cook broccoli as directed but do not drain.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour in a greased casserole dish. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour, stirring twice during cooking time.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp amandine
directions: Saute almonds in butter until lightly browned.
Add shrimp and saute about 5 minutes until shrimp are pink.
Add broth, vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice and pimentos.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Serves four.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles.
Mix in chicken mix, 2 cans of chicken a la king and 1 can of cream of chicken soup.
Pour into casserole dish; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage roll
directions: Cook rice and drain.
Fry ground beef and drain.
Add onions, green pepper and salt, then add a little catsup.
Combine all ingredients; drain and add a little brown sugar.

title: chocolate fluff frosting
directions: Cream butter and 3/4 cup powdered sugar; blend well.
Add vanilla, chocolate and salt; mix well.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Add powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, blending well.
Continue beating until mixture stands in peaks. Add the chocolate mixture and fold in gently, only to blend.
This makes a large amount and easy to spread.
(Three and a half tablespoons of cocoa and 1/2 tablespoon butter equal 1 square of chocolate.)

title: oriental skillet
directions: Brown 1/4-inch thick cutlets in hot butter over medium heat. Set aside.
Add green onions and garlic to skillet.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add broth and lemon-pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Add cutlets.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until cutlets are tender.
Stir occasionally. Add broccoli and water chestnuts. Simmer 5 minutes. Remove cutlets and vegetables to platter.
Keep warm.
In a cup, stir together cornstarch and water. Stir into juices in skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Allow to cook about 1 minute.
Pour over cutlets and vegetables.

title: italian sausage dip
directions: Remove sausage from casing and crumble meat into frying pan. Discard casings.
Brown meat and then remove to a separate dish. Place onion, pepper and mushrooms in same frying pan (add a little oil, if needed).
Cook until just tender.
Cut tomatoes into large chunks and add to mixture.
(Don't add all of the liquid from the can.)
Add the sausage
and spices.
Simmer for about 10 minutes. Add tomato sauce and simmer a little longer.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound veal with mallet until 1/4-inch thick.
Coat veal with seasoned flour.
In large frying pan, melt butter and cook veal on both sides until golden brown. Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered, 20 minutes.
Remove to platter and spoon sauce over veal.

title: chocolate angel dessert
directions: Whip up egg yolks and beat egg whites until they form peaks. Melt chocolate and mix with egg yolks.
Then blend with egg whites.
Fix Dream Whip.

title: picante shrimp 'n peppers pasta
directions: Cook and drain pasta according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add shrimp, peppers, mushrooms, garlic and basil.
Cook, stirring frequently, until shrimp is cooked through and peppers are almost tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes and picante sauce. Simmer 2 to 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add pasta; mix well. Serve with Parmesan cheese and additional picante sauce.

title: country crust yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in sugar, salt, eggs and 3 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turn greased side up and let rise until double. Punch down and make in rolls or loaves of bread.
Let rise again and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate tree truffle
directions: Place whipping cream (do not whip) and butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a full boil.
Stir; let mixture boil up again.
Remove from stove; add full pound of chocolate.
Stir until completely melted and smooth.
Let set up overnight in a very cool place or cover mixture and refrigerate after pouring in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Using a small ice cream scoop or melon baller, make balls.
Roll in Macadamia nut bits or coconut, etc.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook broccoli.
Combine soup, mayo, eggs, onion and cheese.
Put into a greased casserole dish. Sprinkle crackers or crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and pasta
directions: Fill large pot with water.
Bring to boil.
Add salt and oil. Add broccoli and boil about 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti and continue to boil both for about 7 minutes.
Drain all but 1-inch of water.
Toss to mix.
Add cheese and enjoy.

title: strawberry glaze
directions: Mix together and cook until thick.
Add red food coloring as desired.

title: christmas eve soup
directions: Saute onions and beef until beef is brown.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer at least one hour.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Cool completely. Poke holes in cake with end of wooden spoon.
Dissolve jello with 1 cup boiling water. Pour over cake.
Refrigerate. Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate. Serve.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: In large bowl, mix sugar, salt and cocoa.
Add unbeaten eggs and mix well.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add coconut and nuts; mix.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Real easy to make and good!)

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Cool.
Add all other ingredients. Mash Ritz crackers fine and put on top.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: clam sauce
directions: In a saucepan combine celery, clam juice, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes; add water if too thick.
Stir in clams, chives, parsley and oregano.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on cooked linguini.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then 375° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook peas and beans separately, according to package directions; drain well.
Layer peas, beans, mushrooms, pepper and cheese in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers, reserving 1/2 cup cheese.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Use 7 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients and pour in buttered baking dish.
Pour on topping.

title: mustard glazed pork tenderloin
directions: Wash and dry the tenderloins.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl and stir.
Add pork tenderloins and turn to coat well with marinade.
Marinate 15 minutes or as long as overnight.
Broil or grill tenderloins, cooking for about 10 minutes on one side and turning and cooking about 8 minutes on the other side.
The meat should be only slightly pink.
Slice in 3/4 to 1-inch thick slices and serve.

title: honey wheat carrot cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, honey and eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Stir in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until tests done.
Cool and serve plain or with honey cream cheese frosting.

title: greens sauteed with bacon and lemon
directions: In a large saute pan, heat olive oil and saute the Canadian bacon and garlic clove for 5 minutes.
Add roughly chopped greens and toss to coat.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until the greens are limp, 3 to 7 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Serves 6.

title: coconut cream dessert
directions: Crush crackers until fine.
Melt margarine and mix with crackers.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the pudding with the milk.
Add the softened ice cream and Cool Whip.
Spread over the crackers. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: jiffy tomato stack-ups
directions: Cut tomatoes into slices 3/4-inch thick and sprinkle with salt.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of shredded cheese.
Combine remaining cheese, broccoli and onion.
Place tomato slices on greased baking sheet and spoon broccoli mixture on top, dividing mixture evenly between slices.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese and broil 7 or 8 inches from heat for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: corn noodle bake
directions: Soak a clay pot in water overnight.
When ready to cook, place the corn in the clay pot.
Sprinkle lightly with salt and bake tightly covered for 30 minutes in 450° oven.
Before serving cover with melted butter.

title: french salad dressing
directions: *Taste before adding full amount.

title: meat loaf and side dish
directions: Mix ground beef with other ingredients.
Make into loaf and bake about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Mushroom Scalloped Potatoes.

title: turtle candy
directions: Melt butter, sugar, milk and syrup; mix well!
Cool.
Place nuts on greased cookie sheet.
Pour mixture over ingredients; chill.
Melt chocolate and paraffin and dip nuts.

title: fruit pie #2
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Crumble bread or break into small, bite size pieces.
Mix all ingredients with the bread well.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish which has been sprayed with vegetable cooking spray. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: southwest express chicken salad
directions: Cook onion in oil until tender but not brown.
Add chicken, picante sauce, tomatoes, cumin, salt and oregano; simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Arrange lettuce on 4 dinner plates or large platter; top with hot chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with cilantro.
Serve with additional picante sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat egg slightly.
Mix in next 5 ingredients, then nuts. Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake in 400° oven 15 minutes.
Continue baking 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: crab casserole
directions: Mix together and place in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream together for 3 minutes the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, salt, soda, vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix until smooth.
Batter will be stiff.
Add apples, cored (not peeled) and chopped into pieces.
Add nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in Bundt cake pan.

title: steak in a skillet
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Add water, onion and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and cook slowly 1 hour.
Add carrots, potatoes, pepper, celery, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and peas.
Cook 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Knead with hands.
Form into small balls on an ungreased cookie sheet. Butter bottom of small glass and dip into bowl of sugar.
Flatten ball (add to sugar for each ball).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Spray grill rack with nonstick cooking spray.
Place grill rack 5 inches from coals.
Cover with foil, if you want.
In large bowl, combine turkey with other ingredients, except pitas and tomato.
Lightly moisten hands; shape mixture into 4 equal patties.
Grill 10 to 12 minutes, turning once until cooked through.
Serve burgers in pitas with sliced tomato.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9-inch deep unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Pie is done when center is set.

title: no-bake cocoa drop cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and butter for 3 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Mix well with oats and chopped nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper and cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles as directed and set aside. In a large casserole dish (1 1/2 to 2-quarts), combine soup with milk, mixing until smooth.
Add tuna, peas, onions, salt and pepper.
Add noodles and mix well.
Melt butter in a saucepan, add cheese and bread crumbs and sprinkle over casserole.
If desired, sprinkle paprika over bread crumb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Carefully shell eggs.
Bring vinegar and water to a boil. Add spices if desired.
Place eggs in hot sterilized jars and cover with boiling liquid.
Seal immediately.
Yield about 2 quarts.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Do not brown meat.
Put all ingredients, except noodles, in a greased 1-quart casserole; mix well.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring occasionally.
About 15 minutes before serving, cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Serve beef mixture over noodles.

title: melissa's breakfast casserole
directions: Scrub large potatoes and cut in halves.
Season cut side with salt and pepper.
Place pat of oleo on cut half.
Place seasoned and buttered potatoes, cut side down, on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until crusty on cut side.
Serve plain or with sour cream.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Mix ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes on low until raisins are plump.
Use as side dish to pour over ham. Double or triple recipe depending on amount of servings.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon and drain.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add onion and green pepper to drippings in skillet. Cook and stir until onion is tender. Stir in bacon and remaining ingredients. Cook, uncovered, over low heat about 15 minutes.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Put meat into bottom of pan.
Put vegetables on top of meat. Add soup over top.
Top with mashed potatoes or hash browns. Place in a 400° oven until it bubbles.

title: easy swiss steak
directions: Rub steak with flour.
Season with salt.
Brown in oil in skillet and pour tomato juice just to cover steak.
Sprinkle in dried onion flakes.
Simmer over low heat about 1 1/2 hours.
Turn occasionally and add more liquid, if necessary.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Bring sugar, margarine and milk to a boil in a saucepan.
Boil for about 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in chocolate chips and Marshmallow Creme.
Pour into a pan and cool.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients. Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° until done (about 45 minutes).

title: chili's mexican cheese dip(microwave)
directions: Blend all of the ingredients.
Cook 12 minutes on Medium, stirring every 2 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips and hot sauce.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in double boiler.
Stir in milk.
Cook until mounds on spoon.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Beat egg yolks.
Add some hot mixture; mix well and then add this to the rest of the mixture.
Cook 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, milk, onion, cheese and sour cream. Stir in turkey and zucchini. Add spaghetti; toss to coat. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serve with added cheese, if desired. Makes 4 servings. This is a great way to use the leftover Thanksgiving turkey.

title: baked french toast
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan (or larger if possible). Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over melted margarine.

Beat eggs and milk. Dip slices of bread in egg/milk mixture; place on top of brown sugar. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°. No need to flip while baking. Serve caramel side up; sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Make cake as instructed.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut together.
Pour over hot cake.
Cool cake.
Drain pineapple, spread over cake.
Mix together Cool Whip, sour cream and powdered sugar.
Spread over cake and sprinkle with coconut. Cover tightly and keep refrigerated.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and pour into 8 x 8-inch casserole well greased with bacon fat.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup of boiling water.
Dissolve lemonade in 3 cups of cold water.
Mix.
Add grape juice and ice cubes. When ready to serve, add ginger ale and ice cream.

title: maple sugar cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt or tube pan.
Blend and beat all ingredients, except sugar and syrup, for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: baked vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in large, shallow casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir well.

title: sunny orange slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend until drink is thick and slushy.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: smurf cakes
directions: Mix pancake mix per instructions on box.
Use 1/4 less water or milk than directions call for.
Open blueberries but do not drain.
Add complete can (including syrup) into mix and stir well. Batter should turn completely blue.
Cook per package directions.

title: lite-oven fried chicken
directions: Combine Bisquick, poultry seasoning, celery seed, salt and pepper in paper bag; shake to mix.
One at a time, place chicken in bag and shake to coat.
Place coated chicken on buttered baking sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken, then bake until done.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Debone and cut in bite size pieces. (If using hamburger, cook and drain off grease.)
Cover bottom of baking dish with chicken.
Add garlic and onion.
In another bowl, add the tomatoes and chiles, soup and diced Velveeta cheese.
Stir well.
Pour over chicken.
Add corn.
Crush Doritos and pour over top of mixture.
Bake until cheese melts, approximately 20 minutes, at 350°.

title: cream of veggie soup
directions: Boil cauliflower and broccoli in chicken broth until tender. Add onions and carrots and continue to cook until veggies are tender.
Make a paste of flour and butter; add the milk and cheese.
Add this mixture to the veggies.
Add more broth if the soup is too thick.
Continue to cook until it is the consistency desired.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Drop by tablespoon in greased skillet or on oiled griddle.
Turn when brown on one side and brown on other side.

title: play dough
directions: Dissolve salt in water on slow heat.
Add food coloring, alum, oil and flour.
Work until not sticky.
Keeps well.
Store in airtight container.

title: spinach loaf
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except egg yolk, and blend thoroughly.
Turn into a buttered 5 x 8-inch loaf pan. Set in a larger pan with 1-inch warm water and bake for about 1 hour at 325°.
When done, let cool for a few minutes and then turn out on a heated platter.
Sprinkle with hard-cooked egg. Slice and serve.

title: weight watchers strawberry pie
directions: Cook jello, water and cornstarch until thick.
Cool and stir in berries.
Pour in baked pie crust.

title: oreo pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix pudding and milk; set aside.
In another bowl cream confectioners sugar, margarine, cream cheese and vanilla.
Add to pudding mixture and stir thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip and stir.
Crumble half the cookies on bottom of an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Pour pudding mixture over this.
Cover with other half of crumbled cookies.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: fried whole okra
directions: Cut off stem end and tip of okra pods; wash thoroughly.
Cook in boiling salted water for 8 minutes.
Drain and dry completely. Roll in seasoned cornmeal.
Fry in deep fat (350°) or saute in butter until brown.
Serves six.

title: date cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add eggs and mix.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream. Stir in dates.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 400° oven about 10 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth.
Serve with fresh fruits such as apples and strawberries.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown cheese bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish for 1 hour or until golden brown at 350°.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Heat beans and water to boiling.
Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 1 1/2 hours until beans are soft.
Skim foam.
Remove bay leaf and ham bone. Trim meat from bone. Add to soup. Season to taste.
Add boiled potatoes as an option.

title: vegetable stuffed artichokes
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add shallot, zucchini and eggplant. Season well.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix in crabmeat and season well.
Continue cooking 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese and finish cooking 2 minutes.
Stuff artichoke bottoms with vegetable mixture and top each with bread crumbs.
Broil in oven for 2 minutes until browned.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix according to directions on box.
Make two layers.
Slice each layer into two (four thin layers).
Thaw and drain strawberries.
Mix sugar, sour cream and Cool Whip.
Place between layers of cake.

title: barley soup
directions: Boil meat with bone until very tender in plenty of water and salt.
Cool.
Remove bones and all traces of fat.
Cook with all vegetables and barley until tender.

title: rice krispy treats
directions: Butter 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine in 3-quart saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows.
Stir constantly until marshmallows are melted and mixture is well blended.
Heat about 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press in pan with hands coated in margarine.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: 30 minute casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain corn and beans. Mix all together. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Crust:
Mix 2 cups flour with butter and confectioners sugar until it holds together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Heat and serve with ground beef for Sloppy Joe sandwiches or use over chicken on the grill for barbecued chicken.
Also good with shredded pork for barbecued pork sandwiches.

title: zucchini-beef casserole
directions: Brown the meat and onion in oil.
Pour off excess grease. Add rice and seasonings; stir a few minutes.
Layer in casserole 1/2 the sliced zucchini, meat-onion-rice mixture, cottage cheese, remainder of zucchini, soup and grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: ruth's fudge
directions: Boil the sugar, milk and butter good; after boiling, stir for 9 minutes at a boil.
Take off heat.
Add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cake mix cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to cake mix and flour (you may need to use more flour).
Let rise.
Roll out and spread with your favorite ingredients.
For cinnamon rolls, put in pan and let rise again.
Bake at 370°.
Frost.

title: corn casserole
directions: Add these together and either heat them in the microwave until everything is well blended and the cream cheese is melted, or place them in a casserole and put in an oven until everything is heated.

title: dinner out
directions: Sort through coupons, discarding those past expiration date. Select one from remaining pile.
With telephone directory in hand, locate phone number.
Pick up phone and dial number using pencil, telephone dialer or finger.
When restaurant answers, make reservations, indicating time and number in party.
At this point, ask for directions (men may skip this step).
Add babysitter as needed, applying house instructions liberally.
Using desired mode of transportation, arrive at restaurant.
Select meal, enjoy, pay tab with credit card or cash; top with tip.
Serves 2.

title: popcorn salad
directions: Chop water chestnuts, green pepper, onion and celery.
Mix together.
Before serving, add popped popcorn.

title: easy sausage pizza bake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Cook and stir sausage and onion in 10-inch skillet until sausage is brown; drain.
Mix baking mix with water.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in glass bowl (or other clear container).
Do not mix!
Cream mayonnaise, sour cream and seasonings together.
Spread over salad.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together cheese, 1/2 cup margarine and vanilla. Alternately beat in sugar and 1/3 cup milk.
Blend in chocolate. Remove 2 cups to save for frosting.
Cream together remaining chocolate mixture and margarine.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Beat into creamed mixture alternately with remaining milk.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch cake pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool on racks.
Frost cake with saved mixture.

title: dump it cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread pineapple into bottom of pan.
Pour cherry filling evenly over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Sprinkle walnuts and coconut next.
Cut margarine into slices and cover top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken marinade
directions: If using as a basting sauce, use butter.
If using as a marinade, use oil.
Much better as a marinade overnight.

title: granny's hot milk cake
directions: Heat butter and milk together until butter is melted.
Beat eggs until light and lemon colored.
Add sugar rapidly, beating until smooth.
Add flour alternately with hot milk mixture.
Add vanilla and baking powder last, mixing thoroughly but not for more than 1 minute.
Bake in two 9-inch pans for 30 minutes at 340°.

title: cheesy vegetable chowder
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; bring to boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Stir in corn; remove from heat.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese and cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir cheese mixture into vegetable mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican layered bean dip
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread beans in a rectangular pan until smooth.
Add hot sauce now, if you like a spicy dip, into beans (about 2 to 3 tablespoons).
Add shredded Monterey Jack cheese on top of beans, spreading evenly.
Bake until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.
Smooth sour cream over melted cheese, then shredded lettuce, shredded Cheddar cheese, tomato, green onion, olives and optional jalapeno for extra spicy.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: chicken diable
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in shallow pan.
Stir in honey, mustard, curry powder and salt.
Add chicken and turn to coat.
Bake, uncovered, about an hour, turning once.
Baste frequently until chicken is tender.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together in a very large mixing bowl the soups, pimentos, corn and sour cream; rinse soup cans with small amount of water and add to browned meat.
Cook noodles; drain and add to mixture.
Butter casserole; pour in mixture.
Top with cracker crumbs and butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a bunch.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat butter and sugar until soft and creamy.
Add pecans and flour.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 30 minutes or until barely turning color. Roll while hot in confectioners sugar.
When cool, roll again in confectioners sugar.
Makes about 40 (1 1/2-inch) balls.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Beat butter lightly.
Gradually add powdered sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Put nuts and candied fruit in large pan. Add flour and coat well.
Add butter mixture.
Mix well.
Add brandy.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put crushed crackers on top and add melted butter.
Bake in preheated oven, 375°, for 30 minutes or until toasted. Deeelicious.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. (Do not cook the rice first)
Add sticks of butter. Put in 9x13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: exotic spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach; drain on paper towels.
Tear into smaller pieces.
Combine all ingredients; store in plastic bag. Refrigerate.
Tastes even better the second day.

title: peach butter
directions: Peel peaches.
Remove pits and spots.
Place in kettle with water and cook until tender.
Rub through sieve and measure.
To each cup of pulp, allow 2/3 cup of sugar.
Add spices.
Cook until thick, stirring frequently.
Pour into sterilized, hot jars and seal.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain real good.
Mix remaining ingredients. Reserve some Cheddar cheese for top.
Top with cheese and chopped, crumbled bacon.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until top is brown.

title: penuche
directions: Cook sugar and milk over low heat; stir constantly until boiling.
Put candy thermometer in.
Let go to 234°.
Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Wrap in wax paper.
Put in refrigerator; will keep several weeks.

title: chopped broccoli a la grecque
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook 2 minutes.
Uncover; break up vegetables with fork.
Simmer, uncovered, until liquid evaporates. Should be no draining.
Yields 3 servings.

title: party sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients well and form into 1-inch balls. Bake 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet until golden brown.
Makes about 6 dozen balls.

title: yummy corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven about 50 minutes or until set.
If desired, omit melted butter and instead dot top of pudding with butter before baking.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pare 6 medium apples.
Slice thin and add to cooked mixture.
Toss lightly to mix.
Spread evenly over crumbs; pat remaining crumbs over apples.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: baked carrots and onions
directions: Arrange carrots and onions in alternate layers in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with salt and pepper.
Top with butter; pour white sauce over all.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix the orange juice, vanilla wafers, powdered sugar and melted margarine.
Form into balls.
Roll in coconut.
Very good for that special occasion.

title: aunt sharon's pink (blue) stuff
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Chill for 4 hours.

title: hawaiian chicken(method:  foil)
directions: Prepare foil.
Dip chicken in soy sauce until all surfaces are coated.
Place in center of foil.
Place remaining ingredients on top of chicken.
Wrap tightly and place chicken down in coals (check after 30 to 45 minutes for doneness of chicken).

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Saute onions, bell pepper and celery in margarine.
Add parsley, garlic and shrimp or crawfish.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add flour, cream and cheese; simmer 30 minutes.
Boil and drain pasta while mixture is simmering.
Add pasta to mixture and pour into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add boiling water while stirring constantly, using high heat until mixture begins to thicken.
Then cook slowly on low heat until thick.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook 2 minutes longer at low heat.
Add lemon juice and rind. Pour into a baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: chocolate covered peanut clusters
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients
in
heavy
saucepan
over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add peanuts and drop spoonful onto waxed paper;
chill.
Store in container and keep in refrigerator.

title: no toss salad
directions: Place lettuce in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle next 3 ingredients in layers on top of lettuce.
Break peas apart and sprinkle on top while frozen.
Spread mayonnaise on top of peas and sprinkle with sugar.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add layers of bacon, eggs and tomatoes.
Sprinkle generously with cheese.
Do not toss.
Cut into squares.

title: green junk(pistachio dessert)
directions: Fold pistachio pudding into the whipped cream.
Add cherries, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill and serve.

title: coco-not cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, and coconut flavoring together.
Add egg and mix well.
Add Bisquick and potato flakes, mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Drop tsp. drops onto ungreased cookie pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield about 4 dozen.

title: spicy vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic.
Brown ground beef.
Mix other ingredients; simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits, slowly stirring into boiling water, for 2 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let sit for 5 minutes.
Melt Velveeta cheese and butter.
Blend in egg and add to grits together with Tabasco; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; sprinkle with paprika and crumbs.
Cook in preheated oven at 325° for 20 minutes.
Double recipe to serve 14.

title: carrot-banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan. Sift first 4 ingredients in medium bowl.
Mix oil, brown sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in carrots, bananas and nuts.

title: whitney's favorite cookies
directions: Put peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers, like a sandwich. Melt chocolate according to directions, then put cookies in, one at a time, using a spoon.
Next, place on wax paper and drop M&M's on top; then let dry.

title: chili rice
directions: Brown meat and onions in saucepan and drain.
Put in a cooker. Add all other ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: mary's chicken packets
directions: You will need foil.

title: easy cheese log
directions: Soften cheeses.
Add dry dressing mix; mix well.
Shape into log; roll in chopped pecans.

title: cocoa frosting
directions: Prepare the frosting in a saucepan.
Combine butter, cocoa and milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Mix in powdered sugar and vanilla until frosting is smooth.
Pour warm frosting over cake or brownies as soon as taken out of the oven.
Cool.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, form into ball.
Roll in pecans. Sprinkle with pepper.

title: apple raisin mallow crisp
directions: Place apples, raisins and water in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt. Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly, then scatter over apples. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are done and topping is crisp. Remove from oven, place marshmallows over the top and return to oven until marshmallows are melted and lightly browned.

title: pinwheels
directions: Blend cream cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce and horseradish until smooth.
Lay out 5 slices of meat, slightly overlapping on 18 inch piece of aluminum foil.
Lay out 2 more rows to form rectangle.
Spread with mixture and roll up as for jelly roll. Chill.
Before serving, slice into one inch slices.

title: southwestern chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts in large pan.
Coat the chicken with barbecue sauce and place on a cookie sheet.
Chop the green pepper, onion and tomato; mix together and put on top of chicken. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake in a moderately hot oven to melt (5 to 8 minutes).

title: almost snickers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Return to foil-lined Alba package. Freeze.
Makes 1 serving.

title: chocolate peppermint pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt; add gradually to hot milk.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook 5 minutes longer.
Blend half of the custard with melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add gelatin to remaining hot custard; stir until dissolved and let cool.
Add sugar slowly to stiffly beaten egg whites and fold into plain custard, adding peppermint flavoring. Place chocolate custard in bottom of baked pie shell.
Let stand until slightly
firm.
Cover with peppermint custard and stand in refrigerator or cool place.
When firm, cover with whipped cream and sprinkle with grated chocolate.

title: cauliflower-ham au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange cauliflower in rectangular baking dish.
Sprinkle with ham.
Beat soup and milk until smooth; pour over ham.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake until topping is golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry sour cream nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a mixing bowl and set aside.
In a separate, larger bowl, cream the sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, then cream and vanilla.
Stir dry ingredients into liquid mixture quickly until just moistened. Fold in berries and nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured 8 x 4-inch loaf pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: grammy dow's coffee chip bars
directions: In medium bowl, cream shortening and brown sugar.
Add egg and coffee.
In large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt. Add wet ingredients to dry.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan at 325° for 15 to 18 minutes.
May be frosted.
Cut into bars.
May be doubled for 13 x 9-inch pan. Serves 12.

title: beef and pork neckbone soup
directions: Boil beef and pork neckbones in a large pot until tender or meat falls off the bone.
Remove the bones.
Add tomatoes, frozen mixed vegetable soup mix and white potatoes.
Let cook until vegetables and potatoes are done.
Serve with cornbread or crackers.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Put cooked broccoli in casserole dish.
Mix soup, Cheez Whiz, milk and rice; pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cooked and diced chicken, ham or turkey may be added for 1 dish meal.

title: hungry jack beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Stir in salt, beans, barbecue sauce, brown sugar, onion and heat until bubbly.
Pour into casserole dish.
Place biscuits on top and sprinkle with cheese.

title: oven-fried eggplant
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Slice eggplant in 1/2-inch slices.
Beat egg.
In bowl (flat bottom), combine crumbs and seasonings.
Dip slices in egg, then in crumb mixture.
Place on preheated cookie sheet that has been greased with 1 tablespoon Crisco.
Continue coating slices and adding to hot cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes, turn over and bake 15 more minutes.

title: lasagne(low-fat)
directions: Mix mushrooms, onion, green pepper and Ragu in saucepan.
Cook beef (drain and wash).
Cook noodles.
Layer noodles, beef mixture and cheeses.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: robin's eggs mexicana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well eggs, butter, flour and baking powder.
Mix together cottage cheese, Jack cheese and green chiles; add to egg mixture.
Pour into well-greased quiche pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Slice tomato and place on top; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add beans, rice and taco sauce.
Cook slowly (low heat) for 3 or 4 minutes.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Layer chips, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Cut chicken breasts in strips.
Dip in mixture of flour, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Dip floured pieces in buttermilk, then dip again in flour mixture.
Deep fry until done.
Drain.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add enough water to juice to measure 1 cup (including lemon juice).
Heat liquid to boil.
Stir in Jell-O.
Break up cranberry sauce with fork and stir into Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate until Jell-O begins to thicken.
Stir in pineapple, nuts, apples and celery.
Pour into 4-cup mold. Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° until bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: egg pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Arrange bacon overlapping along bottom and up sides of casserole about 8 1/4 inches in diameter and at least 6-cup capacity.
Top bacon with cheese.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper until smooth.
Pour over cheese in casserole and dot with sour cream.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until eggs are firmly set in center.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8. Great for holiday brunches.

title: steak and cheese
directions: Cook the steak in a frypan.
Add the mushrooms and then you put the cheese on the sub roll and then you add the steak and mushrooms, then you eat.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar; spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and 1 cup sugar; spread over cooled pretzel layer.
Cool again.
Drain juice from 1 package of strawberries. Combine jello and water; cool and add strawberries.
Chill until starting to set.
Pour over Cool Whip layer.
Be sure jello is cool or it will melt the layer below.
Keep chilled.

title: mexican seven layer dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
In square pan, layer items, starting with bean dip.
Chill, then serve.
Best used with Tostitos.
Measures are approximate; may add or decrease according to your taste.

title: asparagus flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain asparagus and lay in greased pie dish. Add onion and bacon.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Make loaf and bake 45 minutes.

title: horseradish salad
directions: Mix lime and lemon Jell-O with hot water.
When Jell-O is syrupy, add other ingredients.
Put in an oiled mold and chill.

title: mango bread
directions: Stir together the flour, baking soda, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in eggs and oil.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 1 buttered loaf pan (9 x 5 x 2 1/2-inches).
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with milk; add sour cream; add Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and bananas.
Pour mixture over and refrigerate.

title: cheesy chili
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Chop the onion and add to the ground beef.
Drain the kidney beans and add to mix; also add soup and chili powder.
Cook slowly for 1 hour.
If a warm chili is desired, add the hot pepper mixture.
Just before serving, add cheese and stir until melted.

title: homemade fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk and bring to a full boil over a medium heat.
Boil 5 minutes while stirring.
Reduce heat and stir in Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and either chocolate chips or peanut butter.
Pour into a greased pan.
Let cool, then cut into squares.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: For better results let jello set overnight.
Make jello with 3
cups
liquid
instead of 4 cups, using pineapple juice
as part
of
liquid.
Let set until partially chilled, then whip cream cheese with jello until cream cheese is broken up
in
very small
pieces.
Blend in cranberry sauce (do not drain),
drained pineapples and nuts.
Put in a square pan or mold or
individual molds.
If
you want a green crown on it, mix 1
small
package lime
jello and put in bottom of pan or molds.
Let
set
and pour red jello mixture on top.
Decorate with cherries or different types of lettuce.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and coconut. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired. Bake in hot oven (425°) for 25 to 35 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix water and sugar.
Bring to boil and boil for 3 minutes. Put marshmallow cream in large heatproof bowl.
Pour syrup over marshmallow cream.
Add nuts.
Mix well and stir until it loses its glaze.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or wax paper lined pan.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix together pudding mix and milk.
Let set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line 13 x 9-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Layer pudding mix with graham crackers.
Heat frosting in microwave for one minute.
Pour over layer.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Enjoy!

title: quick chicken corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan, cook onion with seasonings in butter until tender.
Add soups; gradually stir in milk and water.
Add chicken and corn.
Heat.
Stir occasionally.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and rice in buttered casserole dish.
Top with cream of mushroom soup, then Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Combine sugar and oil.
Mix and add eggs, one at a time.
Add buttermilk.
Sift flour and soda together and add to sugar mixture.
Add candy, nuts, coconut and dates.
Mix well and pour into tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.

title: rainbow delight
directions: Melt butter, mix with sugar and crumbs.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place toast in baking dish.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Mix eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla, cinnamon and milk together well.
Pour over raisin-topped bread.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: party mix
directions: Mix well.
Bake 2 hours at 250°.
Stir well every 15 minutes.

title: spa salad
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Chop vegetables.
Rinse linguine with cold water.
Add vegetables, dressing and Salad Supreme.
Chill overnight and stir 2 or 3 times.

title: fresh veggie salad
directions: broccoli, mushrooms, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, onion, bell peppers and zucchini.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Step 1:
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix thoroughly.

title: devil swirls
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Cut in grated cheese and butter.
Add milk and mix.
Roll, as for a pie crust.
Spread with ham; roll like a jelly roll and chill thoroughly.
Slice thin.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: duck soup
directions: Put duck in kettle with enough water to cover.
Heat to boiling.
Remove scum from surface of broth.
Put in the next 8 ingredients; cook until duck, vegetables and fruit are done. Remove duck from kettle.
Take meat off bones and put meat back in soup.
Combine 1/2 to 3/4 cup flour and enough cream to make a thin paste.
Add this mixture to soup and let simmer.
The soup will get thicker.
A little sugar or vinegar can be added for taste.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: blender chicken pate
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Peel and chop onions or shallots.
Add to butter.
Cook until tender.
Add chicken livers and apple.
Cook and turn gently until pink.
Add salt and pepper to taste and the marjoram.
Place in blender.
Add eggs.
Blend until smooth.
Add brandy.
Blend again.
Place in small crock. Cool, then refrigerate covered.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: In small bowl, combine nuts, cinnamon, chocolate and 1/2 cup sugar.
In a large bowl at medium speed, beat 1 cup sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour, baking powder, soda and salt (sifted together) and beat at low speed until blended, then at medium speed for 3 minutes. Spread half of batter in prepared pan.
Sprinkle evenly half of nut mixture, then remaining batter and nut mixture on top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes, until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove and serve warm or cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Grease 12 cup muffin tin or line with baking cups.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Combine milk, butter and egg; partially blend into dry ingredients, using about 10 strokes.
Fold in blueberries, just until flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted butter.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Beat butter, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla. Spread on graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Slice bananas and place on mixture.
Spread on crushed pineapple (well drained).
Spread with whipped topping.
Top with cherries and nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pork barbecue
directions: Trim fat from pork.
Puree peppers in blender.
Place pork in roasting pan and pour pepper puree over top. Cook 8 to 10 hours in a 250° oven.

title: thrifty pound cake
directions: Sift together the first 4 ingredients.
Put next 5 ingredients into mixer bowl.
Beat on No. 8 speed for 2 1/2 minutes.
Scrape bowl while beating.
Turn on to No. 3 speed.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Scrape bowl while beating about 2 1/2 minutes.

title: darlene's chili
directions: Brown ground chuck or beef in diced onions and butter; drain. Cook spaghetti as directed on box; drain.
In large pan, put spaghetti and 2 cans tomato juice.
Add hamburger mixture, salt, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, diced tomatoes and beans. Cook until done.

title: grandma's ouellette's hermits
directions: Mix together the butter, lard, sugar, salt, eggs and milk with the soda and vanilla.
Add flour to oatmeal, dates, raisins and nuts.
Mix together until blended.
Drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet (grease first time only).
Bake.
Place cookies in a roasting pan lined with towels, then cover cookies.
Sprinkle with water to keep cookies soft.
Makes 12 dozen.

title: green beans(tangy)
directions: In small skillet, cook bacon as desired and chopped onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: successful pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients; drizzle in butter last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: freeze ahead peach pie filling
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Line 4 (9-inch) pie pans with foil.
Spoon fruit mixture into pans and level.
Place in freezer until frozen solid.
When frozen, close foil, sealing well to prevent freezer burn.

title: moravian sugar cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
To hot mashed potatoes, add 1 cup sugar, 4 tablespoons margarine, 1/2 cup shortening and salt. Add yeast mixture; mix well and let stand in warm place until "spongy."
Add eggs and sufficient flour to make soft dough.
Allow to rise (covered) at least 5 hours in a warm place.
Punch down and turn onto a surface; knead lightly 3 to 4 times.
Spread out evenly in greased biscuit pan.
Let rise for 1/2 hour or doubled.
Punch holes about 2 inches apart; place brown sugar mixture (about 1 teaspoon) and piece of butter into each hole.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir with wooden spoon until moist.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Frost warm cake.

title: mom's chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into 3 parts.
Marinate in the mixture for 24 hours.
Place wings on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, turning chicken over at 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix together; pour into 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle this mixture over top of mixture in Pyrex dish.
Pour 1 1/2 cups hot water over this. Don't stir.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Heat water and oil or Crisco.
Put flour in pie pan.
Pour hot liquid over flour.
Mix with hands.
Smooth crust in pie pan and bake until brown.

title: sand dollars(cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients and vanilla.
Chill overnight.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Roll into small balls and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake on well-greased cookie sheet until brown.
Yields 10 dozen.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Stir baking soda in sour cream; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add flour slowly. Stir in sour cream mixture and vanilla.
Grease and flour cake pan.
Pour in batter and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
In separate bowl work shortening and sugar with a spoon until soft. Beat shortening until light and fluffy, then add eggs and vanilla. Beat until well blended.
Add dry ingredients alternately with a cup of sour milk.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased and floured cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar over cookies. Bake for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: broccoli hot dish
directions: Place frozen broccoli in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour hot water over it (break up with fork).
Stir in rice, soups, onions and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups hot water.
Mix with other ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in dish and congeal; cover with sour cream.
Cover with rest of mixture and congeal.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt in heavy pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it forms a firm ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until smooth and thick.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cool completely.

title: pea salad
directions: In large bowl, combine 1/2 cup wine vinegar, 1/2 cup Wesson oil and 3/4 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Let stand after all ingredients have been combined.
Refrigerate.
Can last 2 weeks.
Can be frozen.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Mix baking powder and egg whites and beat until stiff.
Add sugar and mix well.
Stir in by hand vanilla, pecans and cracker crumbs.
Pour into a well-greased pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool, and then top with whipping cream.

title: whole wheat zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add oil, molasses, light brown sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth and thick.
In a separate bowl, combine the flours, baking soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; add to the egg mixture and stir until well blended.
Fold in zucchini, raisins and nuts.

title: peanut brittle candy
directions: Cook over high heat for 12 minutes.
Stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour onto tinfoil.
When cool, bread into pieces with knife.

title: blueberry pie filling
directions: Mix
all ingredients except butter.
Put in unbaked pie crust and
dot
butter on top.
Add top pie crust and bake at 300°
for 30	minutes
or until golden.

title: christmas morning eggs
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place bread on bottom of pan.
Melt Velveeta and margarine in microwave, approximately 3 minutes. Pour cheese mixture over bread.
Top with cooked sausage.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over mixture.
Chill and cover overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: all-in-one dinner
directions: Mix ground beef with onion soup mix and place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Put uncooked vegetables over the meat. Mix sour cream, cheese, butter and soup together and mix with hash browns. Place over the vegetables. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serves 10 to 12.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Cream oil, sugar and eggs well.
Add the soda to the sour milk, stirring to dissolve.
Add to creamed mixture.
Pre-sift flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Add vanilla, rhubarb and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased bread pans.
Mix white sugar and margarine and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix apples, cranberries and granulated sugar together.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together to make topping.
Spread topping on apple-cranberry mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until berries have popped and mixture is a rich brown.
Serve hot with chicken, turkey or ham.

title: m&m's party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: string bean deluxe
directions: Drain string beans.
Put in baking dish.
Add 1/2 cup of milk and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Sprinkle with dried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: caramel-choco squares
directions: In heavy saucepan put caramels and 3/4 c. evaporated milk. Stir over heat until melted.
Grease and floured a 9 X 13 pan.
In a large mixing bowl put cake mix, margarine, 1/3 c. evaporated milk and nuts.
Squeeze until dough sticks together.
Then press half of dough into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 6-10 minutes. Remove from oven and cover with chocolate chips; then caramel mix. Crumble remaining half of dough mixture over the top.
Bake 15-18 minutes more.
Cool; refrigerate to set caramel layer.
Sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar.
Makes 36 bars.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl. Shape into balls and roll in wheat germ and chill.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box. Add coconut and pecans. Pour cake mix into 9 x 13 pan. In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Drop the cream cheese mixture by teaspoons on top of the cake batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh fruit.

title: ahwahnee tenderloin tips(from fabulous yosemite valley)
directions: Cut meat into thin bias strips 3 inches long.
Brown meat in hot oil; season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle flour over meat, stir and add bouillon, bay leaf and cloves.
Cook, stirring, until sauce thickens and boils.
Cover.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is meltingly tender.
Remove bay leaf and cloves.
In butter, cook green pepper and mushrooms just until tender.
Stir in lemon juice.
Mix and pour over tenderloin tips.
Heat to boiling.
Thicken if necessary.
Trim with pimiento, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter into skillet and add marshmallow cream.
Add 6 drops of food coloring.
Heat on low until melted.
Pour over popcorn and coat well. Form into balls and air dry on waxed paper.
