title: dave's death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cut cooled cake into 3 layers.
Place 1 layer of cake in the bottom of a glass bowl or trifle dish. Spread 1/3 of mousse on cake.
Spread 1/3 of Cool Whip on mousse. Sprinkle with candy.
Repeat this process with other layers. Enjoy!

title: easter bread
directions: Scald milk by heating in a small saucepan until a fine rim of bubbles form around edge.
Stir in sugar, salt and butter.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in large, warm bowl. Add lukewarm milk mixture, eggs, lemon peel and about 1 1/2 cups flour; beat hard until smooth.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a stiff dough.
On a lightly floured board, knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; turn to grease top.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown onions and pepper in butter or margarine.
Combine rest of ingredients and bring to a slow boil.
Let cook 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Package in amounts of your desire.
Can freeze.

title: quick bread pudding
directions: Heat milk. Add salt, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir vigorously. Add vanilla and
remaining sugar. Butter sides and bottom of glass baking dish or casserole.
Put cubed bread in dish.
Pour milk mixture over bread and level off.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: soft punch
directions: In large bowl, mix equal parts of all ingredients.
Add ice and serve.
For hard punch, add rum or vodka.

title: ginger ale pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well after each.
Add vanilla flavoring, then add flour and ginger ale alternately.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: seafoam salad
directions: With fork, in 9 x 13 pyrex dish, mash together pears and cream cheese until it resembles cottage cheese.
In small bowl, dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup of reserved pear juice.
Cool.
Add cooled Jell-O to cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate until soft set.
Whip the cream in small bowl and add to soft set Jell-O, blending well.
Set until firm.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 thin layers.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Unroll towel and spread icing over the whole roll. Save some icing for the sides. After icing is spread, roll cookie fairly tight. After cookie is rolled up, take the remaining icing and spread over both open ends.

title: english muffin loaf
directions: Combine 1 cup of flour, yeast, sugar and salt.
Add water. Beat on low 3 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make very soft dough.
Shape.
Place into well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover.
Let rise 1 hour or until doubled in shape.
Punch down.
Shape into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise for 30 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine margarine and sugar. Add eggs and mix. Add mashed bananas.
Mix soda in the milk and add to the other ingredients. Add flour and nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with silver knife in middle for doneness.
Add extra baking time, if necessary. When knife comes clean, bread is done.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice.
Chop onion and saute.
Chop green and white of green onions and saute.
Fry bacon.
Reserve drippings.
Break bacon into small pieces.
Scramble egg very dry.
Mix all together, except drippings and soy sauce.
Add drippings and soy sauce to taste.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine cereal, nuts, raisins and baking powder.
Stir in sugar.
Mix milk, egg whites and oil together.
Blend with oat bran mixture.
Line muffins with paper baking cups.
Fill with batter and bake 15 to 17 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.
The toothpick should be moist, not wet.
Store in plastic bags to keep moist.

title: crab dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese onto large plate.
Add well drained (important) crab meat sprinkled on top of cheese.
Add the chili sauce and horseradish (mixed together) on top.
Place a double row of crackers around outside rim of serving dish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan, melt a few chocolate chips, butter, Karo syrup and milk and put on top of pie.

title: california cole slaw
directions: Blend sour cream and onion mix.
Add cabbage mixture and vinegar.
Toss until well blended.
Chill.

title: beef jerky
directions: Mix together.
Make ball the size of grapefruit.
Put ball in between wax paper and roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Take off paper. Put on cookie sheet.
Brush with 2 tablespoons of liquid smoke. Bake for 4 hours.
Turn after 3 hours.
Bake at 100°.

title: birds' nest cookies(circa 1940)
directions: Mix butter with brown sugar until thoroughly creamed.
Add egg yolk and blend.
Add flour that has been measured after sifting. Form into balls the size of marbles and roll first in slightly beaten egg white and roll in ground nuts.
Place on cookie sheet and make a small hole in the center of each ball.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; enlarge holes.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: While rice is cooking, pound steak to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Sprinkle with paprika and allow to stand while preparing other ingredients.
Using a large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover in onions and green peppers.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer.
Blend cornstarch, water and soy sauce.
Stir into meat mixture.
Cook until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stir gently.
Heat just to get tomatoes hot.
Serve over fluffy rice or noodles.

title: sulze
directions: Put pork, peppercorns, allspice, bay leaves, onion, parsley, celery, 5 1/2 cups water and salt in kettle to boil slowly 15 minutes.
Add veal and simmer until meats are tender, 1 1/2 hours. Remove meat and grind.
Strain stock and reduce to 2 1/2 cups. Soften gelatin in remaining water.
Add to hot stock and stir until gelatin is melted and stock is cool.
Add vinegar and mix. Combine ground meat and stock mixture and put in 8 1/2 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch pan.
Chill overnight.
Top with lemon juice.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: In a 2-quart glass dish or bowl, combine sugar, syrup and salt.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add pecans and stir.
Cover and microwave on High for another 4 minutes.
Stir in vanilla and butter.
Add baking soda and stir quickly.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Allow to cool, then break into pieces.

title: mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and put into saucepan.
Cover potatoes with water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook until tender.
Drain and then mash.
Add cream cheese, sour cream, pepper and butter.
Beat until light and fluffy.
If too thick, add a little milk.
Cool. Cover and place in refrigerator.
Potatoes may be used any time within two weeks.
They do not get stiff like other leftover mashed potatoes.
Recipe freezes well.
To use, place desired amount in greased casserole dish; dot with butter (grated cheese) to cover the top.
Bake at 350° until heated through (about 30 minutes).
If frozen, bake longer.
Makes 8 cups or 12 servings.

title: chicken mali kofta
directions: Fry the onions in the ghee or butter until golden brown.
Add the garlic, ginger, turmeric, cinnamon, cloves and a little water. Cook for 2 minutes.
Add the tomatoes and simmer until the mixture forms a thick sauce.
Then add the stock, salt, pepper and chilies and bring to a boil.
Add the chicken and cook, covered until done (about 15 minutes or so).
Add the cream just before serving and garnish with chopped coriander leaves.
May be served with shredded coconut, peanuts, cashews or raisins as toppings (any or all).

title: busy day casserole
directions: In a casserole, stir together the raw rice, soups and water. Lay uncooked chicken pieces on top.
Salt and pepper.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart pan.
Stir in sugar, syrup, and salt. Bring to boil stirring constantly.
Then boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in soda and vanilla.
Slowly pour over popped corn.
Mix well.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Fill pie shells.
Bake at 325° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: simply seafood mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add tomato sauce and stir well.
Fold in celery and seafood.
Pour into shallow glass pan; chill until set.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce with mayonnaise for topping and a dash of paprika, if desired.
Yields 4 servings as main dish salad, 6 servings as side dish. Preparation Time:
10 minutes.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Cook beef and onion until brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato soup, oregano and garlic.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook noodles per package directions.
Drain.
Combine with beef mixture in a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven for 3 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Amount of vegetables used depends on size of baking dish. Have potatoes, tomatoes, onions and zucchini in equal amounts.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and diced onion.
Add cinnamon, allspice, cloves and brown sugar.
Moisten with catsup and flavor to taste with Worcestershire sauce.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together in small saucepan.
Cook until sugar is dissolved and all ingredients well blended.
Store in refrigerator.

title: carrots-picquante(copper pennies)
directions: Cook carrots until tender. Drain and cool. Cut onion and green pepper in round slices. Mix with cooled carrots. Mix other ingredients together and pour over vegetable oil. Cover and marinate for 12 hours in a covered glass container. Drain and serve.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Start with lettuce.
Arrange in layers (1 to 7) and top with almonds.
Chill overnight.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Baking dish.

Cut up the loaf into cubes and place half the cubes in the bottom of the baking dish. Place half the cheese cubes over the bread, make another layer with the remaining bread then another layer of cheese.
Beat together the eggs, milk and maple syrup, pour over the bread and cheese. Cover and refrigerate over night.
Preheat the oven to 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4. Bake uncovered for 30-40 minutes until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.
Let it stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Serve warm with butter, margarine, powdered sugar and additional maple syrup.
Serves 10.

title: escalloped chicken
directions: Mix all together and save a few crackers, mixed with butter, to put on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: salad dressing
directions: Add all ingredients
and beat.
Put in quart jar and store in refrigerator.

title: holiday gingersnaps(makes about 30 cookies)
directions: Cream together butter, sugars, spices and salt.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Add molasses and blend.
Sift together twice: flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to molasses mixture and stir until blended.
Chill well.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon jello cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve lemon Jell-O with water as directions state on box. Grind in food grinder
oranges and cranberries.
Add all to Jell-O and refrigerate.
Very good with any meat dish.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and sugars.
Add egg and vanilla. Beat until creamy.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Put into greased little muffin pans.
Do not press into pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Fry the Italian sausage and tear into small pieces.
Beat eggs and salt.
Add sausage and cheese.
Pour into hot skillet with just enough oil to scramble eggs.
Stir constantly until done. Set off heat.
Lay out the tortillas and spoon about 1 scrambled egg on each.
Fold ends over, then roll up into a burrito.
Make ahead and refrigerate until needed.
Just heat in microwave about 10 to 15 seconds.

title: crock-pot steak
directions: Put steak, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot. Stir well to coat. Add other ingredients. Cover and cook 8 hours on low or 5 hours on high. Serve over rice.

title: rainbow fruit salad
directions: In large bowl stir together sweetened condensed milk and lemonade using medium speed of electric mixer. Add remaining ingredients. Stir by hand until fruit is well coated. Store in airtight container in refrigerator.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve citric acid in the boiling water.
Mix remaining ingredients together.

title: farrell's favorite barbecue ribs
directions: Wipe ribs and place in a roasting pan.
Blend all ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake in a moderate oven (350°) about 1 1/2 hours, uncovering during the last 30 minutes.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size chunks and stew over medium heat 14 days or until tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 3800 people.
If more people are expected, add the rabbit, but remember very few people like to find a hare in their soup.

title: sour cream rolls
directions: Soften margarine.
Sift flour.
Mix margarine, sour cream and flour.
Grease tins.
Fill tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: best baked beans
directions: Cook beef and sausage until well done.
Crumble with fork while cooking.
Drain fat.
Cook bacon until crisp and crush over other meats.
Open beans and drain juice.
Mix meat and all other ingredients with beans.
Bake in a Pyrex or other oven bowl at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: nachos
directions: Spread bean dip lightly on tortilla chips.
Top with cheese and the jalapeno peppers.
Place 10 chips at a time on paper plate.
Cook on 70 (Roast) for 30 seconds or until cheese begins to melt.
Serve hot.
Makes 30 canapes.

title: chocolate peanut butter honey balls
directions: Mix together.
Shape into 1-inch balls and dip into melted chocolate.
Let sit until chocolate cools.

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: Remove shucks and silks from corn.
Put into large pot and cover with water.
Add salt, sugar and margarine.
Let boil 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in a tightly covered container at room temperature.
For each serving, stir 4 level teaspoons of mixture into a cup or mug.
Add 3/4 cup of hot water.

title: picture frame eggs
directions: Butter both sides of bread slice.
Cut out center of bread slice with a round cookie cutter.
Heat griddle.
Place bread slice on griddle.
Crack eggs and pour into hole in bread slice.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When bread slice is browned, flip over and brown other side.
Remove when egg is cooked.

title: peach delights
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 2 round cake pans.
Drain peaches, save juice.
Add enough water to reserved juice to make 1 1/4 cups.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, salt, then add zucchini.
Beat again, then mix flour and baking powder.
Heat pan with oil on medium heat on stove or you can use electric skillet at 350° temperature.
Then drop with spoon in pan and fry until brown that edge, then turn on other side.

title: scottish scones
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into a nice dough with milk.
Roll out and cut into shapes.
Bake on a thoroughly well- heated griddle.

title: casserole
directions: Place in layers.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: green beans and carrots amandine
directions: Cut each carrot lengthwise into quarters.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, cook carrots, beans, bouillon and 1/4 cup water, covered, on High 12 to 14 minutes in microwave until vegetables are tender-crisp, stirring twice.
In 1-cup glass measure, cook almonds and butter on High 2 1/2 to 4 minutes until almonds are lightly browned, stirring once.
Toss vegetables and their liquid with almond butter and lemon juice.
Serves 4, about 140 calories per serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain.
Line greased 2-quart casserole with 6 tortillas and pour in meat mixture.
Mix beans, sauce and chicken soup and pour on top.
Top with cheese and 6 tortillas.
Pour over tomatoes and chilies.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hanky panky(sausage snacks)
directions: Crumble and brown sausage in skillet.
Cut up cheese; add to sausage with oregano to suit taste.
Stir well to get all mixed together.
Spread on top of pieces of party rye.
Bake in a 350° oven for 5 to 10 minutes, until just lightly browned and bubbly.

title: arroz con pollo
directions: In an electric skillet, brown washed chicken well on all sides.
Sprinkle rice between chicken pieces.
In a large bowl, combine all remaining ingredients, except peas.
Pour mixture over chicken and rice.
Simmer, covered, 30 minutes.
Scatter peas all over chicken.
Cover and simmer 15 additional minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon pecan refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add lemon juice and rind. Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients. Mix well. Stir in nut meats. Shape in rolls. Wrap in waxed paper and chill thoroughly. Slice very thin. Bake on greased cookie sheet in oven (350°) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix in frying pan the ketchup, onion, sugar, water and sour salt.
Put in tiny meatballs and cook 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally with wooden spoon.

title: spiced pumpkin custard
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light and fluffy; beat in eggs. Stir together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. Combine pumpkin and buttermilk; add to creamed mixture alternately with dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in chopped walnuts.
Spoon mixture into greased and floured 6 1/2 cup ring mold; cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for one hour. Let stand 10 minutes.
Unmold.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: easy cheesy surprises
directions: Leave margarine and cheese spread at room temperature until softened, then mix with flour.
Refrigerate the dough to make it easier to work with.

While it is chilling, prepare the "middles." I use stuffed olives (cut in half and blotted dry), Little Smokie sausages (cut in thirds or fourths), pecan halves, sometimes cocktail onions, whatever you like.
Wrap a spoonful of the dough around each surprise and roll into a ball.

At this stage, they keep very well in the refrigeartor between layers of waxed paper. When ready to bake, put them on a cookie sheet and bake about 15 minutes at 350°; they will be slightly brown on the bottom.
They can be baked ahead of time, and warmed up in the microwave.
These are especially good for teen-age parties; young people love guessing which surprise is inside each one.
Each recipe yields about 3 dozen.

title: heath cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Cover completely with saltines.
Melt butter and add sugar; bring to boil.
Boil mixture 3 minutes (don't allow to turn golden brown).
Pour mixture over saltines and bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Pour 12 ounces of chocolate morsels over.
As they melt, spread them evenly with the back of spoon.
Refrigerate until set; break into pieces and serve.

title: banana mallow pie(a cool and yummy treat for summertime desserts)
directions: Prepare crust as instructed.
When cool, slice bananas thinly onto crust.
Mix pudding as instructed.
When somewhat firm, fold in whipped cream and marshmallows and pour into pie crust over bananas.
Chill for a few hours and serve.
Enjoy!

title: banana split cake
directions: Crust:
Mix 1 stick melted margarine with graham cracker crumbs and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: donut muffins
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll muffins in mix of cinnamon and sugar.

title: congealed strawberry salad
directions: Pour 1/2 mixture in pan or dish.
Let set, then spread sour cream over mixture.
Pour other half mixture over cream.
Put back in refrigerator and let set until congealed.

title: nicaraugan casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Cook first five ingredients together. Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Layer noodles, cheese mixture and beef mixture.
Repeat layers and top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake until bubbly at 350°.

title: norwegian apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine dry ingredients.
Stir well.
Beat in egg and vanilla with whisk.
Stir in apples.
When mix becomes thick, spoon it into a buttered pie plate (8 or 9-inches) evenly. Sprinkle a little sugar on top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
This recipe will marinate 50 chicken wings.
You may also use chicken breasts or legs, etc. Place chicken in a covered container.
Pour marinade over.
Flavor improves if marinated overnight.
Meat may then be baked, broiled or barbecued.

title: grated potato dumplings(pyzy)
directions: Grate potatoes and allow to drip dry in fine sieve or cloth bag.
Gently press out moisture.
Let the leftover liquid settle; pour off the clear liquid at top and add the sediment (starch) to grated potatoes.
Stir in egg and flour and work into a moist but firm dough.
If it feels too mushy, adding a bit of flour won't hurt.
Transfer dough to moist board; form walnut sized balls between floured hands and cook in boiling salted water.
If you want, leave the dough mushy and spoon it out of bowl with a tablespoon into the boiling water.

title: pumpkin preserves
directions: Pour 3 cups of sugar over pumpkin and let stand, covered, overnight.
The next day, add remaining sugar and bring to boil in a heavy kettle.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/4 hours.
Add lemon slices and ginger.
Simmer 1 hour more.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch space at top.
Wipe any spills from jar rims and immediately pour 1/8-inch hot paraffin on preserves.
Yield: 8 half-pint jelly glasses.

title: easy pork chops and rice
directions: Dip both sides of pork chops in flour.
Brown both sides in hot oil or Crisco in layer frypan with a lid.
Drain excess oil. Fill gaps between pork chops with instant rice.
Pour chicken gumbo soup and chicken broth over rice.
Cover and place in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into a buttered 13 x 9 pan.

title: stewed shrimp
directions: Add water if needed.
Over medium heat, saute vegetables until cooked.
Peel and devein shrimp.
Cut in pieces.
Mix with vegetables until shrimp are pink.
Add soups.
Add Old Bay and pepper.
Let simmer 5 minutes.
Add wine.
Serve over rice or grits.
Serves 10.

title: hors d'oeuvre
directions: Drain tuna.
Add softened cream cheese, onion, lemon juice and horseradish.
Mix well.
Roll into ball and cover with nuts. Serve with crackers.

title: munchies
directions: Mix together dry dressing mix, dill weed and garlic salt, then add to oil.
Heat in microwave or on stove top.
Put crackers and oil mixture in sealable plastic bag; toss every 20 minutes for 1 hour.
Let set 3 hours.
Makes 3 to 4 quarts.

title: corn dip
directions: Mix together. Add onion powder, salt and garlic to taste. You also can add cayenne pepper. Serve with corn chips.

title: sweet crisp pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers in about 3/8-inch slices; slice or split regardless of size.
Put in crock.
Pour over salt dissolved in boiling water.
Cover with cloth and let stand 1 week.
A scum may arise, but no alarm if cucumbers are well covered.
After 1 week, drain.
Cover with boiling water and let stand 24 hours.
Drain. Cover with boiling water and alum.
Let stand 24 hours and drain. Make syrup with vinegar and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add spices. Let stand 24 hours.
Drain liquid; reheat and let stand 24 hours. Repeat process for 5 days.
Repeat process and can.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put thawed hash browns on bottom of pan. Mix other ingredients together; spread on top. Top with grated cheese and corn flakes. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cajun rice
directions: Over medium heat, cook rice, garlic and onion.
Cook ingredients in a medium skillet, until ingredients are lightly browned (must stir mixture).
Add 1 good dash of Tabasco sauce while browning.
Add remaining ingredients while stirring.
Bring to a full boil.
Place cover on top and remove from heat.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: quick dessert
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; add chopped bananas.
Blend in bowl with Cool Whip; mix until all fruit is covered.
Refrigerate 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve cold.

title: rice salad(serves 8)
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Cool. Combine cheese, peppers, onion, nuts and pimento in large bowl. Stir in rice. Combine oil, vinegar and pepper well; pour over rice mixture. Toss gently. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours. Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired. May be made the night before.

title: cranberry coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine and add sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with sour cream ending with dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Roll into balls; brown in frying pan. Put into casserole dish and pour 1 can consomme soup over top. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: easy turkey divan
directions: Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Heat oven to 400°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inches.
Arrange broccoli in dish; sprinkle with 2 tablespoons cheese.
Layer turkey slices on cheese.
Mix milk, nutmeg and soup; spoon over turkey. Cut margarine into baking mix and 2 tablespoons cheese until crumbly; sprinkle over soup mixture.
Bake uncovered until golden brown, about 25 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: filet mignon adobo(with red bean ragout)
directions: Drain the beans.
Put beans, water and 1/2 teaspoon of the salt into a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer for 2 hours.
Add more water as needed to just cover the beans as they are cooking.
When the beans are almost done, saute the pancetta or Canadian bacon for 3 to 4 minutes.
To make a sofrito, add the garlic, chili, tomato, onion and remaining 2 teaspoons salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add the sofrito and squash to the beans and cook, uncovered, for an additional 25 minutes, adding water as needed.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks, blend with milk.
Add lime juice and peel. Beat 1 egg white until stiff, fold into milk mixture.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Beat 3 egg whites with cream of tartar until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar, a little at a time.
Continue beating until mixture is thick and glossy.
Fold in 1 teaspoon vanilla flavoring.
Pile meringue on pie filling and swirl it over top bringing it out to pastry rim to seal and prevent shrinkage. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Chill before serving.

title: hot slaw
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from drippings and set aside. Add all other ingredients, except cabbage.
Cook until thickened. Add cabbage; stir, top with bacon and serve.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, dry ingredients, and milk. Add remaining ingredients, stirring just enough to mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 22-25 minutes at 300 degrees.

title: beef and macaroni(serves six)
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
Pour cooked macaroni over meat. Add ketchup, salt and pepper.
Stir well; add soup and mix thoroughly.
Top with cheese.
Put into 450° oven until cheese melts.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Bake pie shell as directed on package.
Beat pudding and pie filling (dry), whipped topping mix (dry), milk and almond extract in bowl until blended.
Beat on high speed until soft peaks form (about 3 minutes).
Fold in cherries.
Pour into pie shell. Refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours.
Top each serving with 1/2 cup reserved syrup.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes in a pan.
Put in hamburger.
Then put on soup. Mushrooms go on top.
You cook it for 31.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Combine ingredients. Mix with mixer on medium speed. Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: spaghetti casserole 2
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain and pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Brown hamburger, drain.
Layer over top of spaghetti.
Pour both cans of soup over hamburger and smooth, covering hamburger. Top with cheese.
Cook in microwave 10 minutes or until cheese melts.
In oven, cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat shortening with butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg yolks one at a time, mixing well.
Combine flour, salt and soda. Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add to batter.
Grease 3 round cake pans.
Pour in batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from the pans and cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle coconut on top.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Cook until a thick consistency.

title: microwave baked beans
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish, cook bacon and onion on High for 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring twice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all but catsup in bowl; form into loaf in the pan that can be baked in.
Cover with catsup.
Bake at 350° to 375° for one hour.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, bananas and pecans.
Pour 1/2 mixture into dish and gel.
Put sour cream on top after it gels.
Pour other 1/2 of mixture on top of sour cream; let gel.

title: taco casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in one cup hot water.
Let cool and congeal some.
Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind berries, apples and oranges.
Stir in sugar and let set while dissolving jello in hot water.
Chill jello until partially set.
Add to fruit mixture and refrigerate to congeal.

title: brownies
directions: Melt shortening with chocolate in saucepan. Combine sugar and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in melted chocolate mixture.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla and nuts. Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt, eggs, oil and 3 1/2 cups flour; beat well.
Gradually add rest of flour.
Knead well. Let rise until doubled (about 2 hours).
Knead again a few times. Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness on floured surface and cut like dumplings.
Dip each piece into melted oleo and drop into tube pan helter skelter (use 2 tube pans or can use cake pans).
Let rise until doubled (about 1 hour).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Delicious.

title: fudge pudding
directions: Mix dry ingredients on low speed.
Add vanilla, milk and butter.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread batter 1-inch thick in pan.
Mix sugar, cocoa and water.
Pour over batter and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 50.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cut in pieces.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, beat eggs slightly, then add all other ingredients (stuffing should be prepared according to package directions).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 45 minutes, or until lightly browned.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: In medium bowl, stir flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. In large bowl at medium speed, beat sugar, oil and eggs until blended.
Add bananas and beat well.
At low speed, beat in flour mixture, just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into loaf pans (2).
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on wire racks.

title: oyster stew
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, cook the oysters in their liquor, on medium heat, until edges just begin to curl.
Add butter or margarine, milk or half and half, salt and pepper to taste.
Heat slowly.
Do not boil.
Spoon several oysters into each bowl and top with milk mixture.
Sprinkle a little paprika or seafood seasoning on each serving, if desired.
Serve with oyster crackers.

title: pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In Dutch oven, place beef and cover with onion mix, mushroom soup and water.
Cover tightly; bake 3 1/2 hours or until tender when tested with a fork.
If desired, 1 hour before roast is done add one ten ounce can of water, potatoes, and carrots.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, 2 at a time.
Add flour in small amounts.
Mix well.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Form together to make a crust.
Bake according to instructions.
Let cool completely. Let cream cheese soften and spread over cooled crust.
Chop peppers and onions and spread over cream cheese.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over all.

title: cabbage tamales or one-dish dinner
directions: To each pound of hamburger, mix:
one cup raw rice, salt and pepper.
Add chopped onion, pepper and celery according to family's taste or omit this entirely.
Shape into tamales.
Wrap in one or more cabbage leaves; pin with a toothpick.
Place the cabbage tamales gently in a cooking pot.
To each pound hamburger, etc., add 1 cup catsup and 1/2 cup water.
Let reach a boil, then cut heat to lowest point.
Let simmer until done or 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Do not stir.
This 1-dish dinner is delicious served with cabbage slaw (using up remainder of cabbage) and hot corn bread or rolls.

title: black walnut fudge
directions: Combine first three ingredients.
Cook, stirring constantly, until candy thermometer reaches 234°.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and chips until well blended, then add marshmallow cream and walnuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans.
Cool; cut into squares.
Makes 6 pounds.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Combine margarine, oil, baking cocoa and water in saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a rapid boil, stirring constantly.
Combine buttermilk, eggs and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat well.
Add cocoa mixture alternately with flour mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Pour frosting over hot cake.
May omit frosting if preferred.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: black cocoa cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Mix with other ingredients.
Add boiling water slowly.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in metal layer pans at 350° or large glass loaf pan at 325°
about 40 minutes or until done.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with margarine.
Take out one cup of crumbs to sprinkle over the top of the cake.
Add molasses, water, hot water and soda; mix thoroughly.
Add reserved crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: western meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well and shape into loaf dish.
Pour sauce over meat and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Very good.

title: tomato cheese melt
directions: Sprinkle half of the Cheddar cheese and cayenne pepper on each muffin half.
Top with a tomato slice.
Sprinkle half of the Parmesan cheese over each tomato slice.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 4 to 5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: black beans and chicken
directions: Brown chicken in a little olive oil.
Saute garlic and onion. Put in all other ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes with chicken. Pour over rice.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until slightly crisp, about 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix other ingredients together.
Add carrots.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Make several days ahead for best flavor.
Enjoy!

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except French fried onions.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes uncovered.
Top with French fried onions; bake 5 to 10 more minutes.
Should be bubbly.

title: fruit and nut salad
directions: Combine gelatin with boiling water to dissolve.
Fold in all at once the strawberries, drained pineapple, bananas and walnuts. Turn half of mixture into a lightly oiled 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate until this layer is firm.
When firm, spread sour cream over first layer; gently spoon remaining strawberry mixture over sour cream.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Beat egg white stiff but not dry.
Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks and cook until it coats spoon as in custard.
Pour this over jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool until almost jelled.
Add beaten egg whites.
Drain the pineapple; add and blend well.
Fold this mixture into the whipped cream. Cut or break the cake into pieces and pour the cream mixture a fourth at a time until all is used.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut into serving size.
Serve with fresh strawberries or other berries.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: prize christmas salad
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup of hot water.
Add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until partially thickened.
Fold in orange, pineapple, cranberry sauce and walnuts.
Chill until firm.
Makes 1 quart.

title: apple fritters(makes about 24 fritters)
directions: Combine in bowl, milk, egg and margarine.
Add grated orange rind and juice, chopped apples and vanilla.
Sift together cake flour, salt and baking powder.
Stir in milk mixture with a spoon until blended.

title: mexican bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
In a crock-pot, cut up cheese into chunks.
Add beef, beans, relish and Worcestershire sauce. Cook on high until cheese is melted and hot.
Turn to low to keep warm.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours. Drain.
Combine seasoning with vinegar and boil.
Add cucumbers and onions; heat to simmering.
Pack while hot; seal immediately.

title: 1 pot seafood supper
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water in which the pepper and shrimp boil have been added, for 10 minutes.
Add corn; cook 2 more minutes.
Add the shrimp; boil for 4 minutes or until pink.
Drain and serve with cocktail sauce.

title: trail's end chili
directions: Brown meat, onion and peppers.
When peppers are tender, stir in brown gravy mix and add 1/2 pot coffee.
Stir until gravy is mixed.
Lightly chop tomatoes and add.
Add tomato paste and beans.
Add remaining 1/2 pot coffee and use chili powder to suit your taste.
Bring to a boil while stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients until you can roll in your hands in 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Options:
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar or thumbprint and fill with favorite jelly. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes until edges are brown. Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: macaroni and cheese(to serve 100)
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Melt butter.
Blend flour and salt. Stir in milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Add cheese to milk sauce.
Mix macaroni and cheese sauce.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until brown.
Serves 100.

title: lo-cal fruit salad
directions: Fold in all ingredients and keep refrigerated.
